INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(62860, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wonderful news!\n\nI will make sure these souls are well taken care of here in Ardenweald.', 37474), -- Return Lost Souls
(62239, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Serves them right for leaving this unattended.\n\nI am sure we can find other uses for it.', 37474), -- Rodent Removal
(61079, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is satisfying to know that the Jailer\'s share now belongs to us. Well done, Maw Walker.', 37474), -- The Jailer's Share
(60762, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is perhaps... ethically questionable to benefit from these motes, given their source. \n\nBut such knowledge may prove vital in defeating our enemies.', 37474), -- Death Motes
(63043, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<With the rending traps disabled, the souls here should stand a better chance of escaping their captors.\n\nThough they may never escape the Maw, at least they have a chance of escaping the grim fate of becoming a mindless shade.>', 37474), -- Sundered Souls
(63179, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are in your debt, Maw Walker.\n\nI don\'t know if we will ever escape this place, but you have at least bought us a chance to strike back at our foes.', 37474), -- Drowned and Torn Asunder
(60175, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mmmm, it smells just like how I remember it! Maybe a little stale, but you won\'t hear me complaining about a job well done!', 37474), -- A Taste of Tirna Noch
(62453, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You know I appreciate hard work, but it\'s important to take care of yourself from time to time. Hope you had fun, blew off some steam, and are ready to get back at it!', 37474), -- Into the Unknown
(62866, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent Maw Walker. Our armies here will grow stronger with each soul you return.', 37474), -- Return Lost Souls
(61983, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your contributions fuel our conquests on the battlefield. The final victory will be ours!', 37474), -- Replenish the Reservoir
(51796, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our war has only begun.', 37474), -- The Battle for Lordaeron
(53372, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Alliance moves against the Undercity, seeking retribution for the burning of Teldrassil.\n\nWe will not allow them to take what is ours, $c.', 37474), -- Battle for Azeroth: Hour of Reckoning
(62606, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ooh, that\'s the stuff all right. It\'s bitter, sure, but wonderfully complex and subtle undertones. Mm! You\'ll have to try some sometime.', 37474), -- A Blackthorn Blend
(60438, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A quiet has overtaken the glade, the leaves no longer rustle in anguish. This is your doing, and we will not forget this kindness.', 37474), -- Challenges in Ardenweald
(60419, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve heard many tales of your greatness, the Winter Queen is quite pleased! \n\nPlease take this, and keep up the fight!', 37474), -- Troubles at Home
(62296, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was close. Those pests can quickly blast away whole chunks of Ardenweald if we aren\'t careful. We\'ve got enough problems on our hands as it is!', 37474), -- Into the Unknown
(60153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a good thing you were there. The gorm have been very hungry lately, and I do not appreciate being nibbled on. Never been my thing!', 37474), -- Into the Unknown
(62615, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The little misses should be safe for now. Their purpose is vital to Ardenweald, and I won\'t have any more of them dying on my watch!', 37474), -- Hyphae Patrol: Gossamer Cliffs
(62546, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It brings me joy to see more souls freed from that dark place.\n\nThank you Maw Walker, for continuing to help us.', 37474), -- No Wisp Left Behind
(63047, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Chains? Not exactly hard to find around here... wait, those runes...\n\nYou have a keen eye, indeed. The magic here is worth further study.', 37474), -- Acquisition: Runeforged Shackles
(63045, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite the tale, $n. Few motivations are as potent as revenge.', 37474), -- Feed Your Soul
(60158, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems our partnership has become rather permanent. Cartel Ve will not rest until we are both eliminated.\n\nI suppose now would be the time to share one of my most important rules with you.', 37474), -- Rule 7: Betrayal is Inevitable
(63154, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An interesting artifact indeed, Maw Walker.\n\n<Ve\'nari gently taps the armor.>\n\nYou can almost hear the screams of the souls who were consumed to forge it.', 37474), -- Shadehound Armor Plating
(63069, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It would seem that Cartel Ve has not given up their pursuit of the Maw.\n\nYou did well to bring me this pathfinder\'s journal. Whatever the cartel has learned about this place will surely serve us better than it would a corpse.', 37474), -- What They Know
(63050, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Intriguing. I had often wondered what differentiated the Cauldron\'s protectors from the rest of the Mawsworn.\n\nI hope these weren\'t too difficult for you to procure.', 37474), -- Acquisition: Blazing Ingots
(62214, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A small victory, Maw Walker. Many more will be required.', 37474), -- Forces of Perdition
(61984, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The anima you have provided will nourish our precious groves. We thank you.', 37474), -- Replenish the Reservoir
(62382, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'She seemed nice. The Mushroom Kingdom, was it? Hmph, never heard of it. Things kids get up to these days....', 37474), -- Into the Unknown
(62610, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmph, serves them right. Think they can go stomping around my grove? I am the only one who gets to do any stomping! I am the one who stomps!', 37474), -- Hyphae Patrol: The Stalks
(62425, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have shown rare bravery, $n. For this the forest recognizes you. Let all know your ferocity in defending our borders, and the love you have for our charges.', 37474), -- Veilwing Soul
(60545, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you have arrived.\n\nWe need heroes like you in this dire hour.', 37474), -- Shadowlands: A Chilling Summons
(61874, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you have arrived.\n\nWe need heroes like you in this dire hour.', 37474), -- Shadowlands: A Chilling Summons
(62544, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you once again, Maw Walker.\n\nThese souls are finally free of the torment and pain.\n\nThere are still so many more, but I am optimistic that we may yet save them.', 37474), -- From a Dark Place
(61075, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, Maw Walker. The Jailer\'s eyes are dangerous, indeed.', 37474), -- A Spark of Light
(60775, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Next time, ask me how to run a stampede of mawrats off the edge of a cliff. That never fails to entertain.', 37474), -- A Suitable Demise
(63039, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Ebon Blade monument radiates with energy from the fallen knights\' runeblades.\n\nIt is a small tribute to their sacrifice, but it will have to do.>', 37474), -- A Monument to Vengeance
(63166, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have... saved these souls from a terrible fate.\n\nEven a... true end... cannot be worse than this torment...', 37474), -- A Shadowed Fate
(62608, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Feel how luxurious the soil is! I\'m going to savor this for a while. Thank you.', 37474), -- A Royal Treat
(61856, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have a particularly special boon for you, o\' champion of Ardenweald. Are you ready?\n\nThe individual joining our Hunt today is... me!\n\n<Vesperbloom rubs her hands together, grinning.>\n\nIt will be nice to get in some field work!', 37474), -- Adventurer: Watcher Vesperbloom
(62859, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wonderful news!\n\nI will make sure these souls are well taken care of here in Ardenweald.', 37474), -- Return Lost Souls
(62614, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. They\'re still holed up in Darkreach, but that\'s the best we can do for now. Keep \'em contained, and then we\'ll burn them out.', 37474), -- Hyphae Patrol: Eventide Grove
(62607, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at it sparkle and shine! I\'m getting the tingles just looking at it. I feel ages younger already!', 37474), -- Glittering Gritty Goodness
(60437, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have shown courage in the face of great doubt. There are many kinds of strength, and you have shown that you possess one that goes beyond the blade and bow.', 37474), -- Challenges in Bastion
(62611, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There, it\'s done. They should be driven back, if only for a while. I appreciate the help.', 37474), -- Hyphae Patrol: Heartwood Grove
(60388, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well, we will allow them to rest a moment. Today they have learned that even in the calmest meadow, there is always danger.', 37474), -- Training Our Forces
(59937, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work. The lessons you learn from the inimitable Mithdran Dawntracker will last you a lifetime.\n\nNow, down to the business of our quilboar foes...', 37474), -- Taming the Wilds
(55509, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is a truly great thing you have accomplished this day. Be recognized for your sacrifice!', 37474), -- Victory in Wintergrasp
(55511, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lok\'tar! Victory for the Horde!', 37474), -- Slay them all!
(61855, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you again, $p.\n\nYour continued dedication to the well-being of Ardenweald has not gone unnoticed.\n\nQadarin has expressed interest in taking a more active role. Let\'s put his skills to use, shall we?', 37474), -- Adventurer: Qadarin
(60414, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, this is quite a find. These will allow me to procure some rather rare ingredients and materials, and with them, we may turn the tide against our foes. Well done.', 37474), -- Rare Resources
(60381, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our bonds are stronger, our roots grow deeper, due to your actions this day. We will hold strong against the onset of foes that plague us, as groves weave together in defense, thanks to you.', 37474), -- Aiding Ardenweald
(57652, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It really is a remarkable substance. We use it in practically everything! Construction, mending, crafts, and it can even be added to rations.', 37474), -- Supplies Needed: Amber Grease
(62234, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The souls trapped within the power core may yet be saved. Leave me to my research, Maw Walker.', 37474), -- Power of the Colossus
(60646, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your burden is great, but today you have saved souls from damnation.', 37474), -- Misery Business
(63072, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating, the metal here seems to be fabricated entirely of stygia!\n\nThere is much I can do with this. Take this reward, with my thanks.', 37474), -- Acquisition: Stygic Ore
(63062, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve found my siphoner. You are just full of surprises, Maw Walker.\n\nThe unique way that pain and suffering manifests physically in the Maw is a mystery... one which this energy you\'ve collected may help unravel. \n\nWell done.', 37474), -- Torment for the Taking
(62938, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems the greed of the brokers has proved useful.\n\nYou may have acquired exactly what we need.', 37474), -- Information for a Price
(62865, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent Maw Walker. Our armies here will grow stronger with each soul you return.', 37474), -- Return Lost Souls
(63055, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It has been many eons since these portals have been active. It\'s most exciting!', 37474), -- Powering the Portals
(60411, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like this one\'s got a bit more in the head now, maybe they\'ll survive beyond a battle now.', 37474), -- Training in Revendreth
(62287, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do so enjoy the completion of a successful arrangement! The Observer will be pleased.', 37474), -- Observing Arenas
(62314, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Listen up, $n. We need more eyes out there on the battlefield.\n\nThere\'s too many threats, and not enough information flowing our way.\n\nSee if Khaliiq is up to the task. You heard me right, I said more Eyes!', 37474), -- Adventurer: Khaliiq
(60418, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve gotten word from our Kyrian allies that you did them a great service! Thank you!', 37474), -- A Call to Bastion
(61854, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The forest blesses us today, $p.\n\nMaster Sha\'lor says he has sufficiently recovered from his ordeal with the gorm, and would like to be of assistance however he can. He seems especially eager to learn new things.\n\nI guess a little taste of adventure goes a long way.', 37474), -- Adventurer: Master Sha'lor
(61853, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The forest is ever in need, $p.\n\nTe\'zan is as spirited as ever, and perhaps a healthy dose of responsibility will lend him some direction and meaning to his afterlife.\n\nWhere should we send him first?', 37474), -- Adventurer: Te'zan
(61852, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello again, $p. It is good to see you taking such an active interest in the affairs of Ardenweald.\n\nThe honorable Guardian Kota has agreed to work with us, as part of her duties to protect the grove of Tirna Vaal.\n\nTogether, you will ensure the forest\'s continued security.', 37474), -- Adventurer: Guardian Kota
(61553, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They will succeed in their mission, I have no doubt.', 37474), -- Know Where to Strike
(61552, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have much to do.', 37474), -- The Hunt Watches
(62932, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bolvar studies the object intently.>\n\nI sense a familiar essence. The holder of this key may have been involved in the capture of Jaina Proudmoore.\n\nI require time for further research. I will contact you once I determine our next course.', 37176), -- Explore Torghast
(60449, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have heard of your bloody exploits in Revendreth, and I am pleased. \n\nDid you bring me back any of their teeth? No? Well, maybe next time.', 37176), -- Challenges in Revendreth
(60396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our rival houses will think twice before stepping foot outside of their strongholds again. Blood and glory to you, Maw Walker.', 37176), -- Aiding Maldraxxus
(62169, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, Maw Walker. The Eyes place their trust in you.', 37176), -- Eyes to the Sky
(57648, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, Maw Walker.', 37176), -- The Impossible Plan
(61323, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I shall execute Akarek\'s will once more.', 37176), -- See What You've Done
(57644, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for returning me to my sister.', 37176), -- No Friend Left Behind
(61252, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My baroness\'s trust in you is well warranted.', 37176), -- Call In a Favor
(61335, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanks for the rescue! I owe you one.', 37176), -- Rage Against the Cage
(61227, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So you need a mechanic? Well, you\'re in luck!', 37176), -- The Other Foot
(61230, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I appreciate your punctuality.', 37176), -- Outside Influence
(61226, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have suffered so terribly. I must preserve what I still have.', 37176), -- Extra Limbs
(59265, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see cowardice in these eyes. You have done well.', 37176), -- Prying Eyes
(57649, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The baroness inspires great dedication. I trust in her plans.', 37176), -- Whisper of Hope
(58007, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our foes will regret opposing us.', 37176), -- Eyes on the Problem
(62836, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Three sure signs of Anduin\'s presence, yet no sign of him.\n\nThis is dire news indeed.', 37142), -- Signs of the Lion
(61960, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Do you happen to have a spare leg lying around? Surely you don\'t need two. I\'ll put it to good use, kicking your enemies!\n\nNo? I can probably still help anyway.', 37142), -- Champion: Xertora
(63040, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $p. I wondered what had become of that particular associate. \n\nIt pleases me to know that their demise was not a complete loss.', 37142), -- Guaranteed Delivery
(61765, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust you did not let your eyes wander while wearing the soulcloak? It can reveal some truly terrible things...', 37142), -- Words of Warding
(61088, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The curious forms of torment the Mawsworn invent will never cease to amaze me.', 37142), -- Dust to Dust
(63100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The hope of releasing these poor souls from their anguish washes over you.>', 37142), -- Misery's Company
(62563, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You made that look easy. Let\'s hope she learned his lesson this time.', 37142), -- Back Again!
(62256, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, now this is exquisite. Your reconstructed companion said you would be able to come through and you\'ve done so magnificently!\n\nLet him know I\'ll count this toward the repayment of his debts.', 37142), -- Asset Extraction
(60283, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. Your contribution has been logged in our records for posterity to appreciate!', 37142), -- Specter Of War: Visectus
(61509, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Interesting, these are in better condition than most of Chordy\'s finds.\n\nThese will serve us well. Thank you, Maw Walker.', 37142), -- Shinies of Bastion
(62294, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is simply marvelous! This will provide some excellent insight into the history of Margrave Sin\'dane... and possibly something we can use to our own benefit later on.', 37142), -- One Lich's Trash...
(62041, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Suffering is commonplace among those in Revendreth, but you and Roseboil were able to help a few of them nonetheless. \n\nWell done.', 37142), -- In A Bad Light
(62244, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for the supplies. I\'ll see about setting some aside for you at regular intervals.', 37142), -- Digging Around
(62195, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have helped strengthen our forces, Maw Walker.', 37142), -- The Last Word
(62232, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you and Marz have been busy. Job well done, both of you.', 37142), -- Arboreal Tactics
(61523, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Rathan gives Flytrap an apprehensive look.>\n\nThat\'s... that\'s great!\n\nThank you both for bringing back these resources!\n\n<Rathan flashes you a nervous smile.>', 37142), -- Corpse Run
(60410, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, it looks like you drilled some good experience into this one today. Only a few broken bones!', 37142), -- Training Our Forces
(60423, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The cycle will continue, as we have willed it to be so. \n\nWith every foe you slay, the name of Maldraxxus is spoken with glory and purpose.', 37142), -- A Call to Ardenweald
(62364, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. The House of Rituals will learn not to make enemies of the House of Eyes.', 37142), -- Dire Learning
(60230, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many souls, we have much work to do!', 37142), -- More the Merrier
(58211, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You love to see it!', 37142), -- Pumped Up
(62763, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done a great service to not only Ardenweald, but the countless nature spirits we protect.\n\nThank you. Today you are a hero of Ardenweald!', 36949), -- Support the Court
(62867, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A very good collection of souls. Not too broken, not too drained, and not too innocent.\n\nNever fear, their fate is better in our hands than the Jailer\'s.', 36949), -- Return Lost Souls
(60429, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The stories of your power reverberate across the landscape. The bones of the fallen tremble at your name. Let us revel in your victory today!', 36949), -- Troubles at Home
(62308, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven yourself worthy to don the mantle, acolyte.\n\nWear it with honor and pride.', 36949), -- Mantle of Mastery
(61761, 6, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The margrave has been captured? So Kel\'Thuzad has seized control of the house!\n\nThis changes things.', 36949), -- The Better Part of Valor
(61760, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I didn\'t think we would make it out of that encounter intact.\n\nYou are truly a skilled $c, $n.', 36949), -- The Traitor Unmasked
(61759, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have no time to lose!', 36949), -- A Helpful Hand
(61758, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are more resourceful than I thought, $c!\n\nJust a quick incantation, and we\'re on our way to freedom!', 36949), -- Improvised Implements
(61757, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Balmedar\'s voice comes from the adjacent cell.>\n\nThat did not go as planned.\n\nWe need to find a way out of here. The margrave must be warned!', 36949), -- Caught in the Act
(61756, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you managed to procure the reagents from Jor\'dan, and... wait, what\'s this?\n\nI am impressed that you managed to procure the shipment from the brokers when my sorcerers could not!  \n\nYou are quite the resourceful one, acolyte!', 36949), -- Designed to Fail
(61754, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The runes on this blade... they are a hallmark of domination magic!\n\nThis is not good, $c.', 36949), -- No Crate Unturned
(61755, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The guards have been dealt with? Good.\n\nWe have more pressing matters, now.', 36949), -- Blinding the Brokers
(61753, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.\n\nNow we must work quickly, before we are discovered.', 36949), -- Explosive Schemes
(61752, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let me hold onto these for now.\n\nI will need you to get your hands on that shipment!', 36949), -- The Final Reagent
(61750, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This specimen should work nicely for the baron\'s ritual.\n\nI will add it to his parcel.', 36949), -- Heart of the Forest
(61751, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should do.\n\nI will assemble the reagents together to return to your master posthaste.', 36949), -- Cage Free Spores
(62320, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It brings me great relief that your pallid vestments will no longer offend my vision.\n\nDo try keep them in better repair henceforth.', 36949), -- Regalia de Rigueur
(61749, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are Kel\'Thuzad\'s acolyte, are you not?', 36949), -- Necessary Ingredients
(62317, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sorcerer Vutral has been silenced, and with him the suspicions of your ruse.>', 36949), -- Casting Doubt
(61748, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah yes, these will do.\n\nIt will take some time to study these tomes. In the meantime, I have more need of you.', 36949), -- The Hall of Tomes
(61747, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Much better!\n\nI simply cannot abide a disorganized Grimoirium.', 36949), -- Errant Enchantments
(61746, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful. Kel\'Thuzad\'s pets are nothing if not reliable.\n\nWe are done here.', 36949), -- Cantrip Collections
(61745, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kel\'Thuzad always seems to have the most studious of pets, doesn\'t he?\n\nWhat is it the baron wishes of me, acolyte?', 36949), -- Mistress of Tomes
(62297, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, acolyte. The rest should dissipate with time.\n\nTake this, it was left behind by the feckless adept that created this mess. I hope you will put it to better use.', 36949), -- A Fatal Failure
(61744, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There are but a few tasks remaining before we can complete our ritual.\n\nYou must begin immediately.', 36949), -- The Baron's Plan
(61743, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you\'ve returned. I take it the ritual went well?\n\nCome, we have much to accomplish.', 36949), -- The Pupil Returns
(61742, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An impressive resemblance. You may just be able to pull this off.\n\nWell, what are you waiting for?', 36949), -- A Fitting Guise
(61740, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must say it was satisfying watching you wipe the smug look off of Nelesis\'s face. She always thought she was so superior.\n\nBut enough revelry. We have work to do.', 36949), -- Playing Favorites
(61741, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should be sufficient.\n\nLet us prepare for the ritual.', 36949), -- Pilfered Power
(62414, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You left none behind to raise alarm? Good.\n\nWe can proceed with the plan.', 36949), -- Burying Suspicion
(61739, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Balmedar\'s voice resonates from the floating eye.>\n\nYou didn\'t really think I would risk meeting you here in person, did you?\n\nCome, we have much work to do.', 36949), -- The Wayward Baron
(62388, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems we may have our way into the House of Rituals.\n\nDo not mistake this lich for an ally. He pursues only his own agenda. But for now, our goals align... and we can use that to our advantage.', 36949), -- House of Rituals
(62362, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A respectable amount. We will make good use of this.', 36949), -- Volatile Reactions
(62363, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I must thank you. We are no match for the Chosen when it comes to brute strength.', 36949), -- Heavy Lifting
(62864, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent Maw Walker. Our armies here will grow stronger with each soul you return.', 36949), -- Return Lost Souls
(62700, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this should be enough to engrave the runes. Upon lesser equipment, that is. \n\nPotent items will require more... more... Soul Ash. Yes, Soul Ash.\n\nAnd you should hold onto it. I will ask for it when the time comes.', 36949), -- Ashes of the Tower
(61218, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done me a solid, so I\'ll do you one and help ya out.\n\nMe an\' me shovel are at your disposal.', 36949), -- Champion: Dug Gravewell
(61223, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'More! \n\nLet me drink from your enemies! \n\nUnleash me upon them!', 36949), -- Champion: Ayeleth the Deprived
(62999, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Even if it doesn\'t bleed, we can still kill it.', 36949), -- Champion: Croman
(61788, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions on behalf of Revendreth are garnering quite a lot of attention, $p.\n\nSimone has offered to lend her expertise with the mirrors of the Ember Ward to the cause.', 36949), -- Adventurer: Simone
(57919, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That soul is now lost forever. Such wasted potential...\n\nThe Lord Chamberlain will answer for this offense.', 36949), -- An Abuse of Power
(57918, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is worse than I feared.', 36949), -- The Absolution of Souls
(60444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The sins of the doubtful have been purged.', 36949), -- Challenges in Bastion
(60060, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! The mirrors have been attuned and can be used at your leisure.', 36949), -- Mirror Attunement: Pridefall Hamlet
(60147, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! The mirrors have been attuned and can be used at your leisure.', 36949), -- Mirror Attunement: The Eternal Terrace
(63056, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A network of mirrors to translocate throughout the realm will prove invaluable.\n\nRumor suggests of the former mirror maker of the Master was lost in the Ember Ward rather recently. \n\nYou have proven to have a talent for convincing people to join our side.', 36949), -- Sanctum Upgrade: Mirror Network
(61786, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your \"good bud\" Stonehead insists on fighting for the cause, $p.\n\nI\'m sure we can find a use for his skills. Nothing too complicated, of course.', 36949), -- Adventurer: Stonehead
(62935, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good that you saved those tortured souls, $n. A pity none could help our cause. \n\nI must ponder our path forward. You will hear from me again when I know how to best proceed.', 36949), -- Remnants of Hope
(61222, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'Thank you for freeing me Maw Walker.\n\nAllow me to repay your kindness by assisting you.', 36949), -- Champion: Kaletar the Mender
(61334, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A very good collection of souls. Not too broken, not too drained, and not too innocent.\n\nNever fear, their fate is better in our hands than the Jailer\'s.', 36949), -- Return Lost Souls
(63152, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ve\'nari glances over the scroll, rotating it in various directions.>\n\nIt has been some time since I\'ve seen a method of encryption so intricate. But I suppose the venthyr are nothing if not ostentatious.\n\nWhatever the contents of this message might be, it is clear that its author wanted to keep it clandestine.', 36949), -- Venthyr Concordat
(60281, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work. This should keep the both of us safe from the Mawsworn. \n\nI will hold onto the sphere that you found for the purpose of study.\n\nDon\'t you have other matters to attend to?', 36949), -- Rule 4: Make A List
(63340, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. I have heard many stories of your prowess on the battlefield. \n\nI have interest in keeping great combatants like yourself well equipped. Zo\'dash is authorized to further upgrade your armor and weapons.', 36949), -- Sinfall Veteran
(62456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now dat da ol\' boss be a captive audience, he and I goin\' ta be makin\' some new arrangements. Ya best be goin\' now, but don\'t worry... I be seein\' ya soon!', 36949), -- De Other Side: Dealin' Wit' Da Boss
(60146, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have braved torments beyond most mortals\' understanding, $n.\n\nWell done indeed.', 36949), -- Torment Chamber: Thrall
(61962, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'I shall wield my blade with purpose once more!\n\nDeath to your enemies!', 36949), -- Champion: Velkein
(60399, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya did a good thing today, an\' we\'re safer for it. Never been one to give a compliment, me, but today I gotta say ya did a good one.', 36949), -- Aiding Revendreth
(60441, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those that have no masters have learned a lesson today.\n\nWe are their masters, in the end.', 36949), -- Challenges in Ardenweald
(58376, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This ingredient can help construct a very powerful abomination. You should save it incase we find a use for it.', 36949), -- Construct Part: Necromantic Oil
(58624, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The battle has only just begun.', 36949), -- Pauldrons of Imperium
(58608, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Banished One... The Pauldrons of Imperium...\n\nThis lich, Kel\'Thuzad, meddles with powerful forces.', 36949), -- It's Treason, Then
(58472, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let this prove our sense of honor.', 36949), -- A Farewell to Arms
(58599, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done.', 36949), -- Drive A Dredge Between Them
(58523, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have arrived. Let us not dally.', 36949), -- You're Dead To Me
(58504, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The pleasure is mine.', 36949), -- Accusatory Missive
(60721, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anima is flowing to a ward once more. You will want to return to the device periodically and channel more.\n\nAs you gather anima and channel it into Revendreth, the flows will grow stronger. Though they will not last for long right now, eventually you will be able to reinforce the channel, making a permanent connection.\n\nWith anima flowing into our lands once again, it is only a matter of time until we unite all of Revendreth under our banner.', 36949), -- The Anima Must Flow
(63066, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is time to begin restoring anima to the Shadowlands.', 36949), -- Sanctum Upgrade: Anima Conductor
(62161, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re just in time. I\'ve received a missive.', 36949), -- Blood from a Bone
(62313, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! Step closer, come, come!\n\nI\'ve just received word that none other than Rencissa the Dynamo is on her way here to fight for you. Rencissa! The Dynamo!\n\nWho should we have her kill first?', 36949), -- Adventurer: Rencissa the Dynamo
(60482, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You can kill more of them if you want.', 36949), -- See With My Eyes
(61729, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rahel has arrived from Darkhaven to assist us with, and I quote, \"killing anybody.\" She is quite eager to enter the fray.\n\nShe seemed rather upbeat at the prospect of working with you again, $p.', 36949), -- Adventurer: Rahel
(59319, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The mission will be a complete success, I have no doubt.', 36949), -- Advancing Our Efforts
(63064, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have much to accomplish, and as resourceful as you are, you are not able to be in all places at once.', 36949), -- Sanctum Upgrade: Command Table
(60272, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Freedom. Of a sort. Yes... this is good. You have my thanks.\n\nWhat was it you wanted? Ah, power. Yes. Very well, then.', 36949), -- The Weak Link
(60271, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your success continues to impress, Maw Walker.\n\nThough I admit, such feats are becoming less unexpected as I come to know you more.', 36949), -- A Grave Chance
(60270, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Breaking a prisoner\'s chains? I\'m not sure I know how that could be done, unless...$b$bIt\'s dangerous, but I believe there may be a way.', 36949), -- A Damned Pact
(60269, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s been an age since I knew anything other than the contours of this hellish prison.\n\nThank you, mortal. Now to aid you.', 36949), -- Reawakening
(63158, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An intriguing piece of currency.\n\nI would be most interested to learn how it was minted...', 36949), -- Wailing Coin
(60390, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stability in Ardenweald will serve us as we move against the enemy. This was a solid strategic choice, Maw Walker.', 36949), -- Aiding Ardenweald
(63051, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cartel Ve was asking you questions about me?\n\nI\'m flattered. Make sure you never tell them anything.\n\nEver.\n\nCome. There\'s work to do.', 36949), -- Trust Issues
(60268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You could be the key to my freedom. Will you help me, mortal?', 36949), -- Deep Within
(60267, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As you place the key into the device, it shudders for a moment and begins to unlock.>', 36949), -- Prison of the Forgotten
(61099, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finding Baine was no easy feat. But you braved the horrors of that tower and succeeded.\n\nWell done.\n\nBut I fear your work is only just beginning.', 36949), -- The Search for Baine
(60136, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, Maw Walker, what are you waiting for?', 36949), -- Into Torghast
(63033, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have dire news, $n.', 36949), -- The Highlord Calls
(62915, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good choice. \n\nIt\'ll take some time for the construction work to finish, but good fings take time don\'t they?', 36949), -- Home Improvement
(62914, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oi! Wut\'s \'at, then? New souls, is it? \n\nRight, they \'ave a bit of potential, they do. Many fings I can do \'round \'ere wif their \'elp.', 36949), -- A Coalition of the Willing
(62870, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, so you were successful. As I knew you would be.\n\nNow, let us put these souls to use.', 36949), -- Souls for Sinfall
(62837, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! The darkness of the Maw lingers upon you. What news do you bring?', 36949), -- Hopeful News
(60289, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'One of your associates was taken into Torghast? \n\nIt sounds as if he put up quite the fight. Perhaps he could also prove useful... if he were to be rescued.', 36949), -- Rule 3: Trust is Earned
(61355, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should be enough to hide us from the Jailer\'s sight.\n\nI need you alive. For the time being, at least.\n\nNow, back to business.', 36949), -- Rule 2: Keep a Low Profile
(60287, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You seem to have a knack for drawing the Jailer\'s attention.\n\nThis changes the terms of our arrangement.', 36949), -- Rule 1: Have an Escape Plan
(62882, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Take care of that Soulkeeper. I have no desire to go through the effort of procuring another.\n\nNow, let us get to business.', 36949), -- Setting the Ground Rules
(62905, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Back again so soon, Maw Walker?', 36949), -- Back into the Darkness
(62904, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleased to speak with you once again, Maw Walker.', 36949), -- The Souls Plight
(62903, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There we go, the anima is safe and secure now.', 36949), -- Into the Reservoir
(62902, 4, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Boss returns the victor! You got any anima on \'and?', 36949), -- Anima is Power
(62691, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya did a good thing today, an\' we\'re safer for it. Never been one to give a compliment, me, but today I gotta say ya did a good one.', 36949), -- A Calling in Revendreth
(62695, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s right good of you to step up and take on this here challenge, it is. We\'ve got a lot of work to do, here in Revendreth, so\'s I hope you\'re ready to get a bit dirty.', 36949), -- A Call to Service
(62857, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you can see, some have already begun to take notice of you.', 36949), -- The Court's Bounty
(62856, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Work with me and your legend will haunt the waking dreams of every venthyr in Revendreth.', 36949), -- Building Your Renown
(60256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now this is quite a find. A functional piece of the mysterious machinery that can be found around the Shadowlands.\n\nLook at how intricate the weaving of the golden orb is, how the energy seems to be contained from somewhere within, yet in a construct that is almost beyond imagining. What could have made such an object? Where are they now?\n\nWe shall begin to investigate with fervor. Do drop in if you find anything similar, and take a reward before you go.', 36949), -- A Valuable Find: Halls of Atonement
(60244, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A tome from Revendreth? Yes, let me see.\n\nIt chronicles the alchemical formulae necessary to form the dredger pools, and various recipes for forming and utilizing the little creatures. They are quite a curiosity, as much a minion as a reagent.\n\nI will gladly take this off of your hands in exchange for a trade. Here, choose.', 36949), -- Trading Favors: Halls of Atonement
(61104, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The end of Grathalax will deal a great blow to the Jailer\'s infrastructure. Well done.', 36949), -- Grathalax, the Extractor
(62390, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will give these to the fleshcrafters. If we don\'t have enough soldiers, we will just have to build some.', 36949), -- Body Count
(62371, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Word of your aid has been sung through the roots. Thank you, friend of the forest.', 36949), -- Tirna Scithe: A Warning Silence
(62739, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome! What brings you to the Heart of the Forest?', 36949), -- Restoring Balance
(63208, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A wise decision. See to it that they receive your aid swiftly.', 36949), -- The Next Step
(62779, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Revendreth stands stronger for your efforts. The Purpose is clear.', 36949), -- Return to Oribos
(59726, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I would have allowed an apology, but he chose treachery and has paid the price.', 36949), -- It's a Trap
(59724, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, he\'s certainly chosen a scenic location for a fight.', 36949), -- The Field of Honor
(59868, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve made some friends today.', 36949), -- Offer of Freedom
(59716, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, well done! I had a moment there when you drank the poison that I feared for you. But you\'re a hearty sort.', 36949), -- Comfortably Numb
(59715, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the Maw Walker! I have heard so much about you.', 36949), -- Message for Matyas
(59713, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This should be enough to knock him out for long enough to take my sinstone.', 36949), -- Active Ingredients
(59714, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, that\'s perfect. He will not be able to resist this.', 36949), -- A Fine Vintage
(62778, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my sincere gratitude for aiding our cause. Together we will see Denathrius\'s hold on our realm broken, and with it win the freedom of my people.\n\nI cannot offer as much as I would like, but I hope it will suffice until our victory is achieved.', 36949), -- Reinforcing Revendreth
(59846, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah. A pity none of these are mine. Still they may prove useful.', 36949), -- Finders-Keepers, Sinners-Weepers
(59712, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Appreciate you helping my friend. Keep this up and I\'ll be in your debt.', 36949), -- The Lay of the Land
(59710, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, looks like the master just left. What timing.', 36949), -- A Curious Invitation
(60178, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice that it all worked out in the end. Thanks for the unintentional help.', 36949), -- And Then There Were None
(60176, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was not sure this task was possible. Very impressive work.', 36949), -- Bring Out Your Tithe
(60177, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, isn\'t that interesting information you\'ve dug up.', 36949), -- Reason for the Treason
(58272, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ugh, vile things. Give them to me and I will see them properly disposed of.\n\nHere, for your troubles. Perhaps this reward will help wipe the filth of these documents from your fingertips.', 36949), -- Words Have Power
(57481, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work, $n. \n\nBigguns can be... a bit much sometimes.', 36949), -- Running a Muck
(57477, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Bootus ready.', 36949), -- We're Gonna Need a Bigger Dredger
(57474, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Got a bit of devourer gunk on it, but it will have to do.', 36949), -- Dredger Duty
(57471, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can smell it from here. Thanks for that, $n.', 36949), -- It's a Dirty Job
(60509, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you decided to get your hands dirty and join us gents in the labor pool.', 36949), -- Not My Job
(60480, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Much obliged. These torches keep the effects of the Endmire at bay. Even scares away the devourers for the moment. Only lasts so long though. \n\nI miss the good ol\' days of only having to worry about manifestations down here.', 36949), -- The Endmire
(60277, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did it then? Fair enough. Now we can all get back to work.', 36949), -- WANTED: Aggregate of Doom
(58996, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So they were defeated? And yet, you still stand.\n\nShame.', 36949), -- Abel's Fate
(60514, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Constantin examines what you have brought him>\n\nWell done. You may make a fine hopebreaker yet.', 36949), -- Hunting Trophies
(60276, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your reward, as promised.', 36949), -- WANTED: Summoner Marcelis
(60470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sabina\'s end has found her. Ash is all that remains.', 36949), -- Setting Sabina Free
(60468, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This looks like it could fit.', 36949), -- Rubble Rummaging
(60469, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They\'ve perished? Are you sure? Who could have done something so cruel...', 36949), -- Safe in the Shadows
(60467, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sabina begins to stir. >\n\nAre... are they back? Help... help me.', 36949), -- A Rousing Aroma
(62189, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wow, this is a real find you have. Here, a heap of Infused Rubies for the bundle, the best you will see here in the ward. And if you see one of my goods you might like, let me know.', 36949), -- Parasol Components
(63037, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And to what do I owe the pleasure of a mortal visiting Revendreth at such an...inopportune time?', 36949), -- Dark Aspirations
(62279, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Revendreth would be most grateful for your aid.', 36949), -- Revendreth
(60459, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The armies of the undying will not fall today, Maw Walker. You emerge victorious once more in the face of great power, impressive.', 36949), -- Anima Salvage
(60433, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Denathrius did not expect us to rally so quickly, to serve our great purpose in the cycle. \n\nHe underestimated our house for the last time, and has paid the price in blood.', 36949), -- A Call to Revendreth
(58260, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now to put these to a useful purpose.', 36949), -- Queens And Future Kings
(57964, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You can kill more of them if you want.', 36949), -- Revenge Is Easy
(57301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You may continue to add as many ingredients as you wish. The more we add, the more we create!', 36949); -- Callous Concoctions
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(59126, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Atticus will set a box aside each week with spare supplies in case you need any of them.', 36949), -- Supply Chain
(58432, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are valuable resources. Thank you, Maw Walker.', 36949), -- Something Old, Something Used
(62216, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You two make quite the team. It\'s good to have dependable comrades in arms.', 36949), -- Training Program
(61522, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Rathan gives Flytrap an apprehensive look.>\n\nThat\'s... that\'s great!\n\nThank you both for bringing back these resources!\n\n<Rathan flashes you a nervous smile.>', 36949), -- Corpse Run
(60274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, you must have been sent by Ta\'rela. We have need of your services.\n\nTrust me, we will make it more than worth your while.', 36949), -- Trading Favors
(59770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The waystone appears to be waiting for something.\n\nYou reach out and touch its surface...>', 36949), -- Stand as One
(59767, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We made it! \n\nIf we can activate this waystone, we just might be able to escape this place!', 36949), -- The Path to Salvation
(60644, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Were it not for your efforts, I am certain my body and soul would be trapped in this forsaken place for eternity.\n\nI owe you my life, $n, and I will fight to my last breath to repay this debt.', 36949), -- Draw Out the Darkness
(59765, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We were fortunate to find the sorcerer who poisoned Baine\'s spirit.\n\nI will need your help breaking its link to the High Chieftain.', 36949), -- Wounds Beyond Flesh
(59766, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This lacks the balance and craftsmanship of a good Frostwolf axe, but it will have to do.\n\nLet\'s get moving.', 36949), -- A Good Axe
(59762, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Jailer has Baine!\n\nThis is worse than we feared...', 36949), -- By and Down the River
(59776, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot say I enjoyed wielding the Helm of Domination. The magic it holds is... unsettling to the dead.\n\nI gladly return it to your care.', 36949), -- From the Mouths of Madness
(59760, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I had almost forgotten the feeling of freedom.\n\nNow, let us take the fight to these fiends.', 36949), -- The Afflictor's Key
(59761, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew I could trust you with this task. \n\nThough we face insurmountable odds, we must try to do what is right.', 36949), -- An Undeserved Fate
(59759, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew in my heart the Light wouldn\'t fail us.\n\nYour presence here is the proof.', 36949), -- The Lion's Cage
(59915, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems your search was a success.\n\nEnough rest. There\'s much to be done.', 36949), -- Soul in Hand
(59758, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Find enough mouths and one of them is bound to speak. \n\nLet\'s bring this thing back to the cave and find out what it knows.', 36949), -- Speaking to the Dead
(59757, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Useless! These souls are far too fragmented to provide us with anything.\n\nWait... what is that?', 36949), -- Field Seance
(59756, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I need time to recover after that battle. Thrall could use rest, too.\n\nWhile we rest, perhaps you and Mograine can seek answers.', 36949), -- A Moment's Respite
(59755, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rest here while you can, $n.\n\nI will tell you what I know.', 36949), -- A Flight from Darkness
(59754, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those images will keep our foes distracted for a time, but they will not give up their pursuit so easily.\n\nWe must make haste!', 36949), -- On Blackened Wings
(59914, 5, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Praise the Light! I... I\'d almost given up hope.\n\n<Jaina looks upon the Ebon Blade knights.> \n\nIs this... all that remains of your forces?', 36949), -- Fear to Tread
(59753, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am loath to leave some of our knights behind, but it is obvious we cannot stand against such foes. \n\nWe must make sure their sacrifices are not in vain.', 36949), -- Ruiner's End
(59907, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our enemy is relentless, but we will continue to drive them back.\n\nStand vigilant, $c.', 36949), -- Mawsworn Menace
(59752, 1, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve been in this place mere moments and already our forces are depleted. It will have to do.\n\nTake this horn. It can be used to call upon the remaining Ebon Blade forces to rally against your foes.', 36949), -- A Fractured Blade
(59751, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not the most ideal of arrivals, but at least we are still in one piece.\n\nI have not seen any sign of Tyrande. Either she landed elsewhere or continued on without us. We should keep an eye out.', 36949), -- Through the Shattered Sky
(34447, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A wise elder of my order once told me, \"True power is the strength to act and the wisdom to know when not to act.\" May those words and the memory of Kaelynara stay with you on your journey, $n.', 36949), -- Kaelynara Sunchaser
(34972, 1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'It took a lot of hard work but we have made a beautiful arsenal here.$b$bSir, I\'ve been able to outfit your soldiers here with new equipment but I\'d like to do more.$b$bI\'d be deeply honored if you would let me work for you in your main garrison.', 36949), -- Armor Up
(34971, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 700, 0, 0, 'The outpost is now fully up and running and we have enough material to outfit an army - your army!', 36949), -- The Only Way to Travel
(34870, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Fine work commander! Your combat skills are clearly second to none. I am honored to be your armorer!$b$bLet\'s get back to the outpost so we can take stock of our new inventory. I saved a few flares to call us in a ride back.', 36949), -- The Lord of the Gordunni
(34860, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 'Alright, that should be the last one we need. $b$bNothing feels as good as knowing you are stronger than your enemy!', 36949), -- Supply Recovery
(34855, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 600, 0, 0, 'Now with the viziers gone the whole Gordunni enchantment trade with the Iron Horde will come crashing down!$b$bWe can now turn our attention to dealing with Morkurk.', 36949), -- Punching Through
(34858, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, commander. With this another stain on my honor has been removed.', 36949), -- Prized Repossessions
(34840, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that we\'re inside we have much to do.', 36949), -- Dropping Bombs
