(60237, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, Maw Walker. This extra anima will tremendously aid our efforts.', 37176), -- Old Stomping Grounds
(62187, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A whole sackful?! Wonderful! I\'ll be sure to put this to good use.', 37176), -- Satchel of Culexwood
(60426, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will always rise to the defense of the Shadowlands, even if we are weakened from within. \n\nYou have shown that no foe is too far to escape the reach of Maldraxxus.', 37176), -- A Call to Bastion
(60765, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and Roseboil have done well to help the survivors from the House of Plagues.', 37176), -- Cure For All Ills
(63206, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Satisfying, is it not?\n\nThe fewer Mawsworn to rise into the Jailer\'s ranks, the better for our continued existence.', 37176), -- Soulless Husks
(60255, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This mask is similar in features to some of the automaton parts we have found in our time here in the Shadowlands. Perhaps it belonged to an ancient civilization? The information we have is scattered and incomplete.\n\nAny further pieces you may find of this sort will help us unravel these great mysteries. There seems to be a greater design to this place than we can see, yet so much of it eludes us.\n\nI will take it off of your hands, in exchange you make take one of our most valuable pieces.', 37176), -- A Valuable Find: De Other Side
(61095, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Undying Army would like to thank you for your efforts in aiding Maldraxxus.\n\nPlease accept a gift in recognition of your service to our cause and our forces.', 37176), -- Supplies from The Undying Army
(62403, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fine amount. There will surely be something useful in this collection.', 37176), -- Boared to Death
(58525, 378, 11, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'You found them! What wonderful insight into the minds of the venthyr.', 37176), -- The Two Sides of History
(62194, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have helped strengthen our forces, Maw Walker.', 37176), -- Fighting Words
(62217, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and Marz work well together. He\'ll take the hit whenever you need him to.', 37176), -- Field Training
(60398, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With your aid, we have once again been able to perform our sacred duties in defense of the Shadowlands. Little by little, we right the wrongs that have sent us awry, that the cycle can begin anew.', 37176), -- Aiding Revendreth
(62213, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew the Maw Walker would deliver.', 37176), -- A Brokered Deal
(60291, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Rathan gives Flytrap an apprehensive look.>\n\nThat\'s... that\'s great!\n\nThank you both for bringing back these resources!\n\n<Rathan flashes you a nervous smile.>', 37176), -- Corpse Run
(60505, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your help is always welcome, Maw Walker.', 37176), -- Spider's Lair
(63343, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see your skills in combat have improved even further. I trust you have made good use of our previous offer? \n\nZo\'dash is now instructed to offer the full suite of his services to you. I look forward to seeing their impact on your performance.', 37176), -- Necrolord Tactician
(62055, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With these I\'m certain we\'ll catch the attention of Sire Denathrius.', 37176), -- Castle Nathria: Getting a Head
(60405, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well well well, kind of surprised you managed to make it back with your trainee intact. Guess you\'re a better instructor than I gave you credit for. Going to keep that in mind.', 37176), -- Training in Bastion
(60111, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our shared knowledge will benefit all of Maldraxxus.', 37176), -- Forging A Friendship
(62406, 574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sense power. Power and ease.', 37176), -- Staff of the Primus
(59020, 378, 11, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Kel\'Thuzad escaped into the Banished One\'s hands, but at least his evil has been driven from Maldraxxus.\n\nWell fought, $p. Now we focus on rebuilding our forces and restoring order to our realm.', 37176), -- The Third Fall of Kel'Thuzad
(58833, 378, 11, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'We were brought together by chance, but now we fight as one.\n\nOur victory today will be one for all Maldraxxi.', 37176), -- Calling in All Favors
(62391, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our forces stand ready.\n\nLet us end this.', 37176), -- Mobilize Maldraxxus
(60416, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The clink of the coins is the sound of secrets being revealed. Many uses, many things I will purchase. More powerful will we become, due to this. A good find.', 37176), -- Rare Resources
(60651, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'FEED ME!', 37142), -- Champion: Meatball
(60057, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Word has spread throughout Bastion of your actions at the Temple of Courage, $n. Xandria sent word that you were to be amply rewarded for your heroism.', 37142), -- Necrotic Wake: A Paragon's Plight
(57245, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These reanimated troops will be put to good use.', 36949), -- Ani-Matter Animator
(62969, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Bolvar studies the totem.>\n\nYes, this could point us to Thrall\'s location.', 36949), -- Lest the Trail Go Cold
(57929, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Decorous and deserved.\n\nI hope this will be the first of many corrupt inquisitors we fell together.', 36753), -- Hunting an Inquisitor
(60128, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Temel has told me quite the tale of your previous adventures together, Maw Walker.', 36753), -- Ready to Serve
(57926, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Archivist Fane\'s eyes light up when you hand him the archives.>\n\nThis is a lot of potential leverage...', 36753), -- The Sinstone Archive
(60487, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yeah, these\'ll last me awhile.\n\nAlright, I\'ll show you the trick to making a barricade quickly...', 36753), -- It Used to Be Quiet Here
(57927, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Cryptkeeper Kassir inspects the pieces of Temel you brought him.>\n\nThey bashed you real good, didn\'t they, Temel? Nothing I cannot fix...', 36753), -- Rebuilding Temel
(60127, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Cryptkeeper Kassir grins.>\n\nSo you finally listened to the Accuser, eh?\n\nBetter late than never.', 36753), -- Missing Stone Fiend
(57928, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The atonement crypts are meant to be used as storage for souls who require additional... processing before their next ritual.\n\nThe Lord Chamberlain\'s idiots are using them like prison cells and treasure rooms. You are doing us all a favor by opening them whenever you find a key.', 36753), -- Atonement Crypt Key
(57925, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some very angry judges recently passed through here.\n\n<Archivist Fane grins.>\n\nTell me everything you did to antagonize them. Don\'t skip a single detail!', 36753), -- Archivist Fane
(57924, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sacrificed more than you realize to save this soul.\n\nI would do it again, because it is right. Do you understand yet?', 36753), -- Ritual of Judgment
(57923, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Absolution does not come easy. Nor should it.', 36753), -- Ritual of Absolution
(57921, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. You are ready for the ritual.', 36753), -- The Proper Tools
(57922, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'His just reward would be the Maw, but this will have to do.', 36753), -- The Proper Punishment
(57920, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Every lost soul must be tended to.', 36753), -- The Proper Souls
(58093, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am already working to undo the Lord Chamberlain\'s mistakes.\n\nYes, you may assist me.', 36753), -- Our Forgotten Purpose
(63160, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I believe I have seen the creatures described in these pages before. \n\nFrom afar, of course. Always from afar.', 36753), -- Korrath's Grimoire: Aleketh
(63137, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ve\'nari laughs as she appraises the cryptogram.>\n\nThis... is a children\'s toy. Brokers use them to teach their cartel\'s encryption methods.\n\nNot to say that this is worthless. Quite the contrary. In a place such of this, even a glimmer of mirth is valuable beyond measure.', 36753), -- Puzzling Cryptogram
(63163, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite the vivid description.\n\nI suggest you consider this a reminder of what will happen should you fail in your efforts against the Jailer.', 36753), -- Tormentor's Notes
(60732, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rejoice in your accomplishment, but do not forget the weight of your actions.\n\nHe is always watching.', 36753), -- Disrupting the Flow
(60455, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He has seen you, and you are now marked. Wear this as a badge of honor. None other could have done what you did.\n\nHe is not afraid, yet, but he will be.', 36753), -- Storm the Maw
(62461, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suspect this will not be your last foray into the Warrens.', 36753), -- Stalking the Warrens
(60285, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Interesting... runes that can detect brokers by using our extracted essence.\n\nLet us hope you were able to stop any further production. I will keep these for study.\n\nAt some point, you will certainly need to walk the nightmarish plains of the Beastwarrens again. My cypher will continue to allow you to do so.', 36753), -- Rule 6: Concealment is Everything
(63022, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not a moment too soon! Those fiends were just about to put the sword to me. \n\nHere, as we agreed, is your payment in stygia. \n\nThough truth be told, I owe you a great deal more than this. I have nothing left to offer... except for wisdom and warnings.', 36753), -- Rule 6 Addendum: Save Me At Any Cost
(63162, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Despite how long I have been here, there is still much about the creatures of the Maw that remains unknown to me.\n\nSometimes I have to wonder if it is better that way.', 36753), -- Korrath's Grimoire: Gyadrek
(63038, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $p. I wondered what had become of that particular associate. \n\nIt pleases me to know that their demise was not a complete loss.', 36753), -- Guaranteed Delivery
(60248, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh my, this is quite a find. It is a catalogue of some of Stradama\'s procured objects, hidden away within her pools of plague. We will make good use of this, to be sure. \n\nChoose something to take with you, you have earned it.', 36753), -- Trading Favors: Plaguefall
(63153, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, a rare bit of insight into the minds of the Maw\'s eternal tormentors.\n\nQuite fascinating... if a bit frightening.', 36753), -- Discarded Torments
(32672, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Don\'t forget to buy your mount while you are here! You can buy one from Zachariah Post here.', 36753), -- Learn To Ride
(59555, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The enemy is licking their wounds! Our troops will hold the line for now, but we should be prepared for more assaults.', 36753), -- Enemy at the Door
(60195, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many powerful souls, this new additional shall bolster our forces greatly!', 36753), -- Build One More
(62448, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions have attracted the attention of the other houses--and those who question their orders.', 36753), -- Securing the House
(62309, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, it is good to see you again!\n\nFollowing your success against the House of Constructs, Secutor Mevix is eager for more action on the battlefield.\n\nDon\'t leave an eager soldier to wallow here. Give him purpose!', 36753), -- Adventurer: Secutor Mevix
(60252, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This memory glass is old, very old. It may be the memory of a soul that moved on many years ago, we can never be certain. What is known is that the knowledge contained within can never be replicated, and soon, will never be seen again.\n\nI will immediately get to work in preserving what of it I can. I must ask that you take your leave now, please choose a suitably rich reward for your efforts.', 36949), -- A Valuable Find: Spires of Ascension
(60249, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A strange bauble, likely from another world. Yet, why would the paragon have brought this with her? \n\nPerhaps when carrying the soul of a child, as a reminder of something she had thought lost within herself? I will ponder this.\n\nYou may choose a reward from our stores.', 36949), -- Trading Favors: Spires of Ascension
(60445, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You stand alone atop a pile of bones, as a true master of combat. You have shown yourself a real Necrolord today!', 36949), -- Challenges in Maldraxxus
(60184, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You do not cease to impress.', 36949), -- Dude, Where's My Necropolis?
(25073, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, young $r.$B$BYa come highly recommended, mon. It\'s nice ta finally be meetin\' ya in person.', 36949), -- Sen'jin Village
(24814, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tha power dat burst forth when tha Sea Witch died was immense. I can use dis power ta enact a vision of places far away.$B$BObserve, youngblood. I want ya ta be here when I make contact wit\' Thrall, perhaps it will be grantin\' ya insight as well.', 36949), -- An Ancient Enemy
(24813, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dat should keep dem at bay.', 36949), -- Territorial Fetish
(24812, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well fought, young $r.', 36949), -- No More Mercy
(25035, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to have ya, $G brotha:sista;.$B$BVol\'jin makes us all proud in dese moments. It feels good ta be tacklin\' threats head on.', 36949), -- Breaking the Line
(24626, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Swiftclaw! Kijara was tellin\' me about him and he sounded like he\'d be a handful. I don\'t mind da challenge - it\'s da spirited ones like dat that be makin\' da bravest and truest companions when real times of need be comin\'.$B$BTank ya, hon. Ya\'ve been very helpful.', 36949), -- Young and Vicious
(24625, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! Dis naga has set us back quite some time, but nothin\' will be holdin\' us down foreva.$B$BIt\'s good ta be havin\' ya wit us, $n. Ya have a fierce heart within ya.', 36949), -- Consort of the Sea Witch
(24624, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c.$B$BIt will be takin\' brave and determined people like you ta drive da Darkspear up again. I hope dere are more people even half as dedicated to come.', 36949), -- Mercy for the Lost
(24623, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank ya so much! They can be vicious when provoked, but most of da time dey don\'t know betta.', 36949), -- Saving the Young
(24622, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice ta see new faces \'round here, mon. It\'s easy ta get ta feelin\' isolated since we left Orgrimmar.', 36949), -- A Troll's Truest Companion
(60393, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are one step closer to returning our supply of souls to a functioning form, Maw Walker. This is an important advancement in the war for Maldraxxus.', 36949), -- Aiding Bastion
(63145, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Quite the find, Maw Walker. Firsthand information from within Torghast is rare and valuable. None who set foot in the tower return to tell the tale.\n\nPresent company excluded, of course.', 36949), -- Shadebound Testimonial
(62966, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am heartened to know that Thrall yet lives. By the Light, we will find him.\n\nI fear for Anduin. Darkness hungers for his soul.\n\nWe must make ready. You will hear from me when it is time to proceed.', 36949), -- Finding a Witness
(62457, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, you succeeded where others, myself included, have failed.\n\nFrom what I hear, that\'s the second time a relic of the First Ones responded to your presence.\n\nI must admit, I haven\'t the slightest idea how you managed it. Interesting. Very interesting indeed.', 36949), -- The Great Vault
(62312, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve got an exciting development today, $n!\n\nYou must have made quite an impression. Gunn Gorgebone, one of the champions of the Theater of Pain, is demanding to join our ranks here. Demanding it!', 36949), -- Adventurer: Gunn Gorgebone
(63031, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah yes, the dormant stygia throughout the Maw will sometimes coalesce into forms such as this.\n\nYou were wise to bring this to me, $c.', 36839), -- Acquisition: Crystallized Stygia
(58092, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A large step in our journey to reclaim the honor of these halls... but not the last.\n\nI shall send word to the Accuser immediately.', 36839), -- Halls of Atonement: Your Absolution
(60139, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Two of Azeroth\'s architects of peace have been recovered.\n\nTwo remain captive.', 36839), -- Torment Chamber: Jaina
(62719, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve collected all the necessary pieces. Now all that\'s left is to combine them.\n\nSpeak with me again when you are ready, and I will create the prize you seek.', 36839), -- The Final Pieces
(60443, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You return victorious, atop a mountain of bloody feathers! Ha ha! Glorious!', 36839), -- Challenges in Bastion
(61510, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Where did you find these? They\'re positively covered in filth!\n\nUgh, that smell! Here, take this and go clean yourself up.', 36839), -- A Bountiful Haul
(60250, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The fools, giving away an object such as this as a mere trinket to be used in battle. Do they not know of its significance? Clearly not.\n\nLet me explain.\n\nThere is much we do not understand about the workings of this world. This city, Oribos, is made of a strange ore that we have not found anywhere else. Who made this place, and why?\n\nRelics of similar make like this are all that we have to tie together the threads of mystery.\n\nWe thank you for this gift. Please, take a treasure.', 36839), -- A Valuable Find: Theater of Pain
(60253, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What sort of tome is this? May I leaf through it for a moment?\n\nWell then, this is quite a find. It represents many years cataloguing everything Nalthor knew about the origins of our world. The many curiosities of this place, from Zovaal\'s domain in the Maw, to the function of this strange city of Oribos.\n\nIt is surmised that they all tie together.\n\nI shall devour it with glee. Come, you may take one of our most prized possessions for it.', 36839), -- A Valuable Find: Necrotic Wake
(63342, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. I have heard many stories of your prowess on the battlefield. \n\nI have interest in keeping great combatants like yourself well equipped. Zo\'dash is authorized to further upgrade your armor and weapons.', 36839), -- Necrolord Veteran
(61959, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'I shall pay my debt to my Maw Walker.\n\nDirect my power against your enemies.', 36839), -- Champion: Talethi
(60622, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do you think he saw that one coming?\n\nThat was an attempt at mortal humor. You may laugh at your leisure.', 36839), -- Eye of the Scryer
(59520, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Working together will benefit both of us greatly!', 36753), -- Plaguefall: Knee Deep In It
(59750, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, you\'re getting some recognition. I hear people talking about how you killed all those bloodtusks!', 36753), -- How to Get a Head
(62462, 1, 1, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, very good! And a million eyes appeared, you say? How frightening! \n\nGlad she\'s gone and the key\'s in my hands now! She used it to break into many a locked door, you know? A very powerful item! Very profitable too.\n\nAnd now it\'s mine!', 36753); -- WANTED: The Key of Eyes
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(58090, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Scrapper Minoire will have to forfeit her spot in the contest.', 36753), -- Side Effects
(59781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Too bad about the last few, but you\'re still here!', 36753), -- The Last Guy
(59867, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, Maw Walker. I shall dispatch Zo\'umlo to retrieve our stolen property.', 36753), -- WANTED: Appraiser Vix
(58088, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know Scrapper Minoire sent you. She always enhances herself to win the fight.', 36753), -- Juicing Up
(58068, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We would be so lost without your help. Truly.', 36753), -- ...Even The Most Ridiculous Request!
(62785, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, Anzio sent you? Hah, and here I was thinking you were just another nosy fan.\n\nYeah, you look like just the $c I need!', 36753), -- I Could Be A Contender
(58431, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We shall all share in this fabulous brew you have created!', 36753), -- Pool of Potions
(59430, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Working together will benefit both of us greatly!', 36753), -- A Plague on Your House
(58794, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done fine work! Just don\'t tell Caleesy about it.', 36753), -- Stabbing Wasteward
(58785, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am pleased with your work!', 36753), -- Smack and Grab
(58750, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are some good tauraluses. Thanks for the help, mortal!', 36753), -- Take the Bull by the Horns
(63132, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ve\'nari examines the writ.>\n\nQuite an interesting way to record one\'s secrets. This may prove a challenge to decipher.\n\nThank you for bringing this to me.', 36753), -- Constellan Writ
(62733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you liked your surprise! \n\nYou find more silver strongboxes, give Ripe Purian tribute!\n\nOh-ho! You want key to my Golden Chest? Ask me about Steward of the Day!', 36753), -- The Sweetest Tribute
(62730, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, this very sweet and ripe. Must use quickly, before it spoils!', 36753), -- Fruit of the Gods
(62183, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oooh, is that my package of flesh eating ooze! I hope you did not get any on your hands, oh a glove, specification of this specific ooze should mean you have only a 25% chance of an adverse effect. The glove should be burned but I will leave that to your discretion. I will inform the locals of your assistance in delivery, even if it was delayed.', 36753), -- A Leaking Box Marked Perishable
(61958, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'New master now!', 36753), -- Champion: Gorgelimb
(63133, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, I have not seen these runes used in quite some time. An ancient broker method of encryption.\n\nThis will be useful should I ever intercept cartel communications.', 36753), -- Shifting Cryptogram
(60242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, quite a find, we rarely get a glimpse into the mechanisms by which the House of Rituals enact their dark designs. I am eager to delve into this tome, purely in the interests of knowledge of course.\n\nYou may choose from some of our procured items as a reward.', 36753), -- Trading Favors: Necrotic Wake
(63059, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With more work, we can establish portals to other necropoli around the Shadowlands.', 36753), -- Blink of an Eye
(62085, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'ve been wondering where my canteen went. Where did you find this, $n? Did you take a drink before returning here?\n\nNo matter, I suppose.', 36753), -- ...Why Me?
(60722, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes! I feel the flow of anima. You will want to return to the device periodically and channel more.\n\nAs you gather and channel more anima to a tower, its connection to our sanctum will grow stronger. Eventually you will be able to reinforce the channel, making it permanent.\n\nWith enough anima flowing throughout Maldraxxus, our armies will be unstoppable!', 36753), -- Tower Power
(63057, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Long have I waited to weave anima across Maldraxxus once more.', 36753), -- Restoring Power
(63134, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Valuable information, indeed. This will help me avoid detection whenever I must leave the safety of the refuge.\n\nI trust you\'ve already committed the patrols to memory, Maw Walker.', 36753), -- Mawsworn Patrol Map
(61057, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Together, we will guard Ardenweald.', 37474), -- By Trials Forged
(62422, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the moth. Such beautiful creatures. Their shape is now yours to call upon.', 37474), -- Ardenmoth Soul
(62561, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re so grateful for all your help, $n. Seeing the Heart of the Forest like this again, full of power? My heart is filled with hope.', 37474), -- My Heart is Full
(60108, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $Ghuntsman:huntress;.\n\nYou have saved Ardenweald from the Drust, and in so doing, protected countless other realms from their darkness.', 37474), -- Drust and Ashes
(60194, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Damn the Drust! This was all a diversion!', 37474), -- The Call of the Hunt
(60193, 1, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, Ara\'lon... even after all he endured, he found a way to smile again... only to...\n\n<Lady Moonberry wipes her eyes.>\n\nThere will be time for tears later. We still need to stop the Drust. For Ara\'lon... and the forest he fought to protect.', 37474), -- Unmasked
(60192, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ha! There\'s nothing left to protect her now. Let\'s finish this!', 37474), -- Their Last Line of Defense
(60190, 5, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well fought. The Wild Hunt will deal with the rest as necessary. There is one more foe for us to vanquish.\n\nAre you prepared?', 37474), -- Assault on Darkreach
(60191, 377, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. The Drust have been dealt a significant blow.\n\nThe spirits of those lost to Ingra Drif\'s treachery can at last be at peace.', 37474), -- Ingra Drif
(60189, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. You are here.\n\nWe are now ready to end the Drust\'s invasion once and for all.', 37474), -- We Strike Now
(59866, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It fills me with joy to know that the spirits lost to the Maw are safe once more.\n\nNone can say what fate has in store for Vol\'jin. The path on which he has embarked has never before been walked by a mortal soul.\n\nYet whatever awaits him, know that your efforts are what made it possible.', 37474), -- Parting Ways
(59856, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Me be feelin\' Rezan\'s essence inside of me... he be trustin\' me wit\' a great gift.\n\nNo matter what be comin\' next, me not gonna let him down.', 37474), -- Rezan, Loa of Kings
(59824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Rezan be needin\' us!', 37474), -- Loa Rescue
(59822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We ain\'t done wit\' dis place yet. Dere be loa trapped here!', 37474), -- Tracking a Wild God
(59805, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All me trainin\' as a shadow hunter been leadin\' ta dis moment. \n\nTrackin\' a spirit inside da Maw and savin\' dem from eternal torture...', 37474), -- Maw Manifested
(59749, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dere be one loa o\' death, $n. And it be ol\' Bwonsamdi. \n\nYa best not forget dat.', 37474), -- One Little Whisper
(59739, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Me got plans older dan you, $r. Slaying Zel\'han mean noting ta me... ya understand?\n\n<Mueh\'zala\'s gaze remains focused on the broken armor in front of him.>', 37474), -- The Problem with Containing a Death Loa
(59742, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah good, ya got me all da livin\' souls I be needin\'.\n\nDon\'t ya be worryin\' about da ones who passed on. Ol\' Bwonsamdi not lettin\' dem go to da Maw.', 37474), -- Delaying the Other Side
(59741, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at all dis mojo! Dis be just what me need ta make little Mueh\'zala talk.\n\nDon\'t ya be worryin\' about da other undead out dere. Ol\' Bwonsamdi got a plan for dem.', 37474), -- Dark Mojo for a Dark Loa
(59732, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'While ya be here, why not help clean up some of da trash outside me Necropolis? For old time\'s sake, eh?\n\nDen we can be dealin\' wit Mueh\'zala.', 37474), -- Something Extra for the Winter Queen
(59731, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ol\' Bwonsamdi knew ya gonna come see me. I got someting ya wanna hear...', 37474), -- An Expected Guest
(63067, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We regrow with hope.', 37474), -- Root Restoration
(60385, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I smell a group of successful hunters, good. Each successful hunt brings us one step closer to a trained hunting pack.', 37474), -- Training in Revendreth
(62423, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah. The heart of the bear! A fine shape. It is now yours, should you choose to use it.', 37474), -- Ursine Soul
(58452, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Even in the afterlife, the legend of Huln Highmountain continues to grow.\n\nYou have done well to secure his aid, $n. Now let our search begin.', 37474), -- Tracking the Shadows
(58451, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The hunt is over. We have prevailed.', 37474), -- Voras, The Realm Eater
(59721, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are just in time. My preparations are nearly complete.', 37474), -- Becoming the Hunt
(58449, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Reldorn hefts the sacs, which bulge uncomfortably.>$b$bSo many? Just how big is this thing you two are hunting, anyway?', 37474), -- Acid Reflux
(58450, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am amazed that this contains so much concentrated anima. You will surely lure a devourer to you with this!', 37474), -- Anima Instincts
(58447, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This problem just got a lot larger. We need a new plan.', 37474), -- Monster Hunting
(58706, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. This confirms my suspicions.', 37474), -- Dressing the Kill
(59258, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now, let us speak of the hunt.', 37474), -- Home of the Tirnenn
(58446, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, yes. I know of whom you speak.', 37474), -- Tracker Tracking
(58445, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thiernax suggests a bold plan. Locating the other former Night Warriors will not prove easy.', 37474), -- Containing the Night
(61171, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If the Thornspeakers have no way to break the curse, then perhaps there truly is no hope for the possessed. These are tidings most dire.', 37474), -- Unbroken Bonds
(61711, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You performed the ritual admirably, but the Gorak Zhar\'s power was too strong for Gweyir to withstand. There is nothing more we can do, I am afraid.\n\nIt seems the masked fae are lost to us after all...', 37474), -- Ritual of Purification
(61710, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Though this bodes ill, I am not ready to give up hope that Ara\'lon survived. He may still be out there.\n\nI will assemble a search party. We will find him and bring him home... no matter what fate has befallen him. Thank you.', 37474), -- The Broken Spear
(61709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This contains everything we need. Give me a moment and I will prepare the reagents for our ritual.', 37474), -- Witch's Satchel
(61703, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, you were able to find enough nox root for the ritual. Unfortunately, we have another problem...', 37474), -- Nox Root
(61143, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It feels good to be out of that cage and back home in my den.', 37474), -- Return to the Den
(61702, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not a moment too soon! I appreciate your punctuality.\n\nMy den is not far away. We should hurry before more Drust arrive.', 37474), -- A Swift Intervention
(58773, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Drust locked me in this cage and dragged Kivarr away! If you release me, I can show you where they went!', 37474), -- The Thornspeaker Captive
(61701, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ulfar sent you to find me? Free me from this cage, and I will do what I can to aid you.', 37474), -- Searching the Grove
(61113, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is the place, but Kivarr is nowhere to be found...', 37474), -- Kivarr's Den
(61102, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kivarr... yes, I have heard of someone by that name. Ara\'lon may know where to find her.', 37474), -- Kivarr the Thornspeaker
(61076, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can sense Gorak Tul\'s dark power seething within this fetish. Handle it with caution, $c.', 37474), -- Into the Flame
(61061, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have come from beyond the veil to seek my wisdom? A long journey indeed...', 37474), -- Ulfar's Guidance
(60934, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Gweyir and Ara\'lon are the only survivors... this is grave news.', 37474), -- Report to Lord Herne
(60928, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gweyir is the only survivor... but she\'s already been afflicted by the Drust\'s cursed magic. \n\nWe can\'t just leave her here. Not like this!', 37474), -- Blackthorn Captives
(60910, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes! We can use these masks to disguise ourselves.', 37474), -- Masks of Deception
(60898, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep your voice down. There are masked fae are nearby...', 37474), -- The Fate of Ara'lon
(62428, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A majestic shape, for certain. It is now yours, should you choose to use it.', 37474), -- Equine Soul
(62560, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re on the right track, $n! Keep doing what you\'re doing and it will be back to its full, glorious, starryness in no time!', 37474), -- Growing in Power
(59071, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Were it not for your aid, Qadarin\'s soul would have been lost forever.\n\nI... I can do no less than offer my aid in return.', 37474), -- Mending a Broken Hart
(59069, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This figurine... I have not seen it since...\n\nI gave this to her when we first became Aspects. Our duties would draw us apart for the first time in our lives. To know that she has kept it all this time...\n\n<Ysera wipes her eyes.>\n\nWe will put it to good use.', 37474), -- A Token of Lost Love
(59068, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have no idea how tempted I am to open this and read it. Let\'s hurry up and create this counter-curse!', 37474), -- A Secret Never Spoken
(59070, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'HA! That will teach those spriggans! You mess with the mistrunner, you get the magical horn!\n\nNow we have the anima we need! And, conveniently, it\'s already attuned to the bad attitude of the one who cast the curse.', 37474), -- A Sacrifice of Anima
(59063, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew Dreyden would have the scroll we need. We don\'t have time to waste!', 37474), -- Curses!
(59725, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Please tell me you are here to help with the spriggan problem!', 37474), -- Archivist on the Edge
(58871, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I bet those spriggan thought this would be pretty funny. Well, we\'re not laughing!', 37474), -- Broken Harts
(58704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I should have never left! He\'s told me time and again that I should face my...\n\nNever mind. I can deal with that later.\n\nThe situation would have been much more dire if the two of you were not here.', 37474), -- The Garden of Night
(58669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully they\'ll get the message and go back from whence they came!', 37474), -- A Little Pruning
(58647, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. This task is much easier with help.\n\n<Qadarin sighs.>\n\nI hope you do not think too poorly of Thiernax. His history with the Night Warrior ritual is rife with misplaced guilt and remorse, but I am certain I can get him to see sense and offer his aid.', 37474), -- Broken Webs
(59008, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Capturing souls is a far more brazen act than the typical spriggan prank. I wonder what has changed...', 37474), -- Spriggan Snares
(58610, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Qadarin watches Thiernax race off. He sighs before turning to you.>\n\nMy apologies. Thiernax may have seemed curt, but there is a reason for his reluctance to speak of the Night Warrior.\n\nIf you have a moment to help me out in the garden, I can elaborate. Then I will see what can be done to convince Thiernax to help your mother.', 37474), -- The Speaker of Elune
(59821, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome news, indeed. I will not soon forget Mueh\'zala\'s transgressions.', 37474), -- Report to the Queen
(59819, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Wild Hunt can handle pushing the rest of them out of the forest. Well done, $n!', 37474), -- Cleansing the Forest
(59818, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re just in time. The Wild Hunt is locked in battle with Mueh\'zala\'s forces.', 37474), -- Gathering The Hunt
(59817, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am not eager to do any favors for Bwonsamdi, but Mueh\'zala\'s actions cannot be ignored.', 37474), -- Winter Be Comin'
(59815, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It all be makin\' sense now. Mueh\'zala be draining anima outta da other wildseeds so he can be wakin\' Dambala and Hakkar before their time.\n\nDa Winter Queen gotta be told \'bout dis before it too late...', 37474), -- Stolen Loa
(59813, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ya did good! But dis be far from over...', 37474), -- Minions of Mueh'zala
(59812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Da tracks lead into da grove up ahead. I got a feelin\' Hakkar and Dambala be somewhere nearby...', 37474), -- Following the Trail
(59811, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So Hakkar and Dambala be da ones gone missing? Hmm... we\'d better find out where dey went!', 37474), -- Taking Inventory
(59809, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to da Other Side!\n\nWhat ya tink, mon? Ya like what I done wit\' da place?', 37474), -- On De Other Side
(61058, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I just know that together we can save Ardenweald and all the spirits who slumber here.', 37474), -- Bound in Dreams
(57583, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ahh, it\'s nice to stretch out again. I\'ve missed this place, you know.\n\n<Marasmius pauses for a moment.>\n\nDon\'t tell anyone here I said that, all right?', 37474), -- Through the Veil
(62536, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, Maw Walker.\n\nYou have brought back a little bit of the light from the darkness.\n\nWe will make this right, no matter how long it takes.', 37474), -- The Lost of Teldrassil
(57463, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hah! I haven\'t felt that young in ages!', 37474), -- My Way or the Hyphae
(57459, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<About time you showed up! Good thing I took care of all those young ones, eh?>', 37474), -- Fighting For Fungus
(57458, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Together we are strong.', 37474), -- Ring Repairs
(57455, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their bodies will nourish the growth and restoration of the fae rings. It is a worthy end for them.', 37474), -- Mushroom For Improvement
(57454, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally, a friendly face! Are you with the Hunt? You don\'t look like you\'re from around here....', 37474), -- Silence in the Stalks
(63073, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmm. Normally we\'d been seeing some mushrooms sprouting by now.', 37474), -- A Mycelial Network
(59242, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My heart aches for Tyrande. The might of the Night Warrior is empowering her to battle these monsters... but it will consume her if we do nothing.\n\nShandris and I will investigate a... promising whisper that I have heard. I shall call upon you when I know more.', 37474), -- Their New Home
(59189, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot fault my mother\'s intent... but she will be consumed before she finds justice for our people.\n\nWe must find another way to bring her back.', 37474), -- The Recovery of Tyrande Whisperwind
(60530, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tyrande must see reason. She cannot save the kaldorei if she remains lost within this darkness.', 37474), -- The Sea of Souls
(60508, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some vile force in this place intends to stop us from finding Tyrande.\n\nIf experience serves, that means we must be on the right track.', 37474), -- On the Trail
(59181, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have seen bits and pieces of this dark realm in my dreams. Tyrande roams this place.\n\nWe must find her.', 37474), -- Into the Maw
(59246, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will trust you for now, $n.\n\nBut should you betray me, I will ensure you endure the same torments I do.', 37474), -- Daughter of the Night Warrior
(62899, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Court of Night, $n. I just know we\'re going to save Ardenweald! Oh, and the rest of the Shadowlands, too!\n\nAnd if we can\'t, and the forest withers away, and the Jailer breaks free from the Maw and plunges all of the realms eternal into crushing despair from which there is no return... \n\nThen at least we can say we had fun trying!', 37474), -- The Endless Forest
(62900, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and Niya will grow together in time. But for now, your training is complete.', 37474), -- A Conduit for Growth
(61550, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Together, we can do anything.', 37474), -- Strengthening the Bond
(61542, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You... have lived a very interesting life.', 37474), -- The Boon of Binding
(61541, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, wow! I love guiding soulbinding! It\'s my favorite duty!', 37474), -- The Forge of Bonds
(58160, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your actions here will echo beyond the veil. Aid the forest, and all mortal worlds may yet be saved.', 37474), -- For Queen and Grove!
(58159, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A fair enough performance! \n\nI think everyone\'s more acquainted with your world and the role you\'ve played within it.\n\nNext time, the set design will be a bit more... prepared. But for now...\n\n<Moonberry nods at Ysera.>\n\nI think your friend wishes to have a word. Don\'t take too long. We still have to hold the final induction ceremony at the Heart of the Forest.', 37474), -- What's My Motivation?
(58158, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can honestly say I have never seen a performance quite like this.\n\nNow... On to our grand finale! A battle for your world that is certain to make the court sit up and take notice!', 37474), -- The Fourth Wall, er, War
(58157, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not bad! Not great, but not bad. Quickly now, we\'ll need to help set the stage for the next act!', 37474), -- Break a Leg
(58104, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh good! You\'re here! No time to rehearse, but that shouldn\'t be too much of a problem.', 37474), -- Show, Don't Tell
(61479, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May this boon aid you in the trials ahead, $p.\n\nBefore our Queen grants you our power and we accept you formally into our midst, there are certain... Traditions which we must uphold.', 37474), -- The Boon of Shapes
(61475, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is going to be such fun!', 37474), -- The Heart of the Forest
(62286, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fascinating. Fascinating indeed. The Observer will be pleased.', 37474), -- Observing Skirmishes
(61730, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Anduin may appear unharmed, but his soul is imperiled.\n\nSylvanas Windrunner cannot be allowed to carry out her plan.', 37474), -- The Captive King
(61961, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'I am prepared for combat!\n\nPut me in the front line, I will be your shield.', 37474), -- Champion: Rattlebag
(59603, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And so, it is as if you had led the battle personally! Impressive work, if I do say so myself.', 37474), -- In Shadowlands Service
(60049, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Emeni and her constructs will make for powerful allies.\n\nThey will, however, need your assistance to reach their full potential.', 37176), -- At Your Service
(58727, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This spot will do great for us. We can build new constructs, and a home for ourselves.', 37176), -- A Place To Call Home
(58671, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We make a good team, $n.', 37176), -- Bottled Up Inside
(58670, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I feel like we\'ve made our point, $n.', 37176), -- The Slaughter Daughter
(59042, 1, 5, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done it, the construct is completed. The Slaughter Daughter lives again!', 37176), -- A Good Heart
(58686, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re almost done! Just one more step to complete the construction!', 37176), -- Weapon of Mass Construction
(58677, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My cold blood warms to you. You may be a suitable ally.', 37176), -- Skin in the Game
(58680, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You should consider a constructed body, perhaps I can design you one someday.', 37176), -- Loose Threads
(58668, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never imagined myself returning to this place.', 37176), -- Find The Way
(58665, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Do not let Emeni\'s sour disposition deter you. Your aid is greatly appreciated Maw Walker!', 37176), -- Rebellious Souls
(63032, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have dire news, $n.', 37176), -- The Highlord Calls
(62761, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well in Maldraxxus. Their path forward is clear.', 37176), -- Return to Oribos
(61996, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have helped strengthen our forces, Maw Walker.', 37176), -- Say The Magic Words
(58515, 378, 11, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'This will be very helpful. It\'s a shame so many people aren\'t willing to share their knowledge. Hoarding it is simply foolish.', 37176), -- Scrounging for Scrolls
(59609, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you\'re settled--there\'s no rest for the weary in Maldraxxus.', 37176), -- No Rest For the Dead
(62848, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our bond will grow in strength over time, but for now your training is complete.', 37176), -- Conduits, What Are They For?
(61388, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'May we prove worthy allies for the battles to come.', 37176), -- A Journey Made Together
(59597, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our shared knowledge will benefit all of Maldraxxus.', 37176), -- Come On, We're Simpatico!
(63003, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m so pleased to see you again, my apprentice!', 37176), -- Collective Soul
(61359, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a Necrolord, $n. We stand strong.', 37176), -- Power of the Primus
(59556, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is our war to win, Maw Walker. It is now yours, as well.', 37176), -- Welcome To Our House
(62748, 113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All who have reported back to me have said the same--you have brought victory upon victory to the House of the Chosen!\n\nOn behalf of all who serve the Primus, you have my eternal gratitude.', 37176), -- Rallying Maldraxxus
(58609, 1, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back to the fight, $n.', 37176), -- Taking The Seat
(63035, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, another blade on our side! And you aren\'t even dead yet!', 37176), -- A Fresh Blade
(62278, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The armies loyal to the Primus need your aid.', 37176), -- Maldraxxus
(62261, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see Guillotine\'s \"negotiations\" were successful.\n\nThank you, Maw Walker. These sharpening stones will be useful.', 37176), -- Grinder
(59293, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He\'s smelly again? We\'ll at least he\'s happy, even if we are not.', 37176), -- Special Formula
(58992, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, if this isn\'t the best batch of marrow I\'ve ever seen! \n\nMama is going to cook you a feast today!', 37176), -- Pie Not?
(62637, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust your battles went well. And that\'s not just a turn of phrase. I know they did. I knew they would.', 37176), -- A Call to Battle
(60342, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, both of you! \n\nGuillotine\'s efforts have not gone unnoticed. I\'ve seen the others redouble their efforts to follow her example.\n\nThank you both, again.', 37176), -- Cut 'Em Down to Size
(62407, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How is it possible for him to smell even worse than before? \n\nUgh. At least he gets results.', 37176), -- Herbicidal Tendencies
(56470, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! This will make something tasty!', 37176), -- Give A Dog A Bone
(61635, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many souls, we have much work to do!', 37176), -- Troubled Souls
(59615, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know this soul, she is strong and very loyal. We would be well aided by building this most unusual construct.', 37176), -- Every Dog Has Its Day
(60257, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... is not what I expected.\n\nIt is similar in appearance to our people, yet so very different. Are there others of our kind out there? Who are they, and where do they reside? Why have they not made contact with us? Or are they hiding themselves purposefully?\n\nIs this a history we knew but have forgotten? I have so many questions.\n\nI thank you for this, it is quite meaningful to us. Please, take a relic of power from the treasury.', 37176), -- A Valuable Find: Sanguine Depths
(59827, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your performance has netted me a nice profit... Zo\'umlo bet poorly.', 37176), -- Bet On Yourself
(60042, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many powerful souls, we must get to work immediately.', 36753), -- May I Take Your Order?
(60041, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We were successful, Chordy is whole again!', 36753), -- Build-A-Bomination
(60048, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have acquired all the resources we needed.', 36753), -- Stitching Time
(63058, 669, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fixed the stitching table? That\'s great! Soon we\'ll be able to build our own constructs!', 36753), -- Abominable Stitching and Me
(63140, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ve\'nari glances over the manuscript.>\n\nThis is truly an ancient document. A pity it is in such poor condition. The secrets it holds must be priceless.', 36753), -- Worn Obleron Etching
(58265, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Grim work, but necessary. May they be reborn into useful vassals of Ardenweald once more.', 36753), -- Blooming Villains
(58267, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see. This is terrible news.', 36753), -- Beneath the Mask
(58266, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it! All the altars are destroyed!', 36753), -- Break It Down
(58264, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You saved my friends!$b$b<Primrose gives you a small grin.>$b$bWe... we make a pretty good team, huh?', 36753), -- Wake Up, Get Up, Get Out There
(63161, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, yes. This will make for a fascinating study.', 36753), -- Korrath's Grimoire: Belidir
(60284, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Beastwarrens, you say... I wonder what they are plotting...\n\nSuch an embarrassment that they were discovered and captured in the first place. It seems Cartel Ve has become quite careless in my absence.\n\nYou have my gratitude for your assistance, as always. I will inform you when I have need of your services again.', 36753), -- Rule 5: Be Audacious
(63157, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How soothing.\n\n<Ve\'nari takes a closer look at the item in her hands.>\n\nI wonder...\n\n<Ve\'nari presses a diamond shaped etching on the side of the box. It clicks into place, then opens to reveal a secret compartment containing a small piece of rolled up parchment.>\n\nNothing is what it seems, Maw Walker.', 36753), -- Box of Torments
(63164, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, Maw Walker. These will allow us to better anticipate the enemy\'s actions.', 36753), -- Mawsworn Orders
(63155, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Ve\'nari raises the map, inspecting it closely.>\n\nAnd these stains--you said they were here when you found it?', 36753), -- Indecipherable Map
(63136, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, yes. These were clearly written by someone in the grip of madness.\n\nThat is not to say that they are nonsense, however. Sometimes, only the insane can see the truth.', 36753), -- Chaotic Runes
(58623, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So much valuable knowledge saved, and it would not have happened without your help.', 36753), -- A Complete Set
(59994, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it... the Volume of Victory! The single most important compendium of Maldraxxus military history ever assembled.\n\nIt must be mine! Uh, ours. I mean ours!', 36753), -- Trust Fall
(60900, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The volumes are not here!\n\nThe Archivist\'s final words must have meant something. A clue, perhaps?', 36753), -- Archival Protection
(58622, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work so far.\n\nAccess to the secret archives is almost ours!', 36753), -- Secrets Among the Shelves
(58620, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done it! The door is unlocked!', 36753), -- Slaylines
(59917, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nicely done. You\'ve bought us precious time.', 36753), -- Kill Them, Of Course
(58621, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that those guardians are dispatched, we can focus on unlocking the door.', 36753), -- Repeat After Me
(58619, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mortal, are you ready to help me save these valuable writings?', 36753), -- Read Between the Lines
(60402, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, good, I can already see this one\'s learned a thing or two today. I\'ll take it from here.', 36753), -- Training in Ardenweald
(57316, 1, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well fought, $Gbrother:sister;! You\'ve begun your rise to the top!\n\nBut keep up with your training and stay ready. In Maldraxxus, there is always a challenger waiting to take your place.', 36753), -- The Ladder
(58900, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have traveled far for this moment.', 36753), -- A Sure Bet
(59837, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Competing in the arena is but one way to contribute to this venture. There are many other tasks to perform, as well.', 36753), -- Working for the Living
(59203, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, you are more valuable than I first surmised.', 36753), -- Leave Me a Loan
(59879, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You must be one of these outsiders I hear so much about.', 36753), -- This Thing of Ours
(58947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve proven yourself worthy! I\'ll see if we can get you into a fight soon!', 36753), -- Test Your Mettle
(59800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice work firing up the combatants. They\'ll remember you helped them... if they survive.', 36753), -- Team Spirit
(58575, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These weapons will be put to good use. Hopefully, we won\'t have to collect some of them again.', 36753), -- Stuff We All Get
(58095, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A spectacular show, Maw Walker.', 36753), -- Theater of Pain: Help Wanted
(57712, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see that they are returned to their proper places for everyone to enjoy.\n\nI appreciate your help in retrieving them, and I hope they were informative.', 36734), -- Suggested Reading
(59596, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m so pleased to see you again, my apprentice!', 36734), -- Collective Soul
(62846, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'When it comes to matters like these, patience is as important as strength. In time, our power will grow vast and unmatched.', 36734), -- Sanctum Improvements
(62845, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could feel the presence of those souls as soon as you brought them here. Their potential will increase our power!', 36734), -- Bringing It All Together
(62844, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have returned, Maw Walker. \n\nGood. We have much to do.', 36734), -- Return to Draka
(62843, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Back again so soon, Maw Walker?', 36734), -- The Soul Contact
(61397, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With your unique abilities, we have an opportunity we\'ve never had before.', 36734), -- Opportunity Strikes
(62839, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You walk with the stride of victory, Maw Walker. Do you bring anima?', 36734), -- Anima is Strength
(62694, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our rival houses will think twice before stepping foot outside of their strongholds again. Blood and glory to you, Maw Walker.', 36734), -- A Calling in Maldraxxus
(62835, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There is much to be done, Maw Walker.', 36734), -- A Call to Service
(62834, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Surrender is the ultimate failure.', 36734), -- Glorious Ambition
(62833, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For the sake of the souls we defend, we must never falter.', 36734), -- A Hero of Great Renown
(63212, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you would return.', 36734), -- Report to Mevix
(57878, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'All is as expected. Trust always in the Arbiter\'s plan.', 36734), -- Choosing Your Purpose
(57877, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have done well. See that you continue to do so.', 36734), -- The Looming Dark
(57876, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have sensed something horrific has happened. Quickly, tell me everything.', 36734), -- The End of the Beginning
(58086, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What has he done?', 36734), -- The Master of Lies
(59644, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should buy us some time and carve us a bit of a path. Now to take advantage of the situation.', 36734), -- Blinded By The Light
(57694, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So few left, but we will make do.', 36734), -- Refuge of Revendreth
(57693, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is only a matter of time before the Master detects my presence. We must be swift and violent of action if we are to stop Sire Denathrius.', 36734), -- Torghast, Tower of the Damned
(57691, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, you are quite resourceful. Give me twenty five of your kind and some proper gear and we could defeat the Master.', 36734), -- A Royal Key
(57690, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I recognize you. Azeroth has been very busy lately, and her champions have been very much at the forefront of events. We must talk as soon as time allows.', 36734), -- Cages For All Occasions
(57689, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So this is the Maw. I can feel it leeching my essence. Be on your guard.', 36734), -- Prince Renathal
(59327, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will sever your head from your body should you...\n\nWait...\n\nYou are still alive? That means you are... the Maw Walker?', 36734), -- In the Ruin of Rebellion
(57724, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that we have cleared out the Master\'s forces, let us continue the search for Prince Renathal!', 36734), -- Securing Sinfall
(60566, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Breakfist is badly injured.>\n\nToo many... couldn\'t make it...', 36734), -- Into the Light
(57461, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Theotar takes a slow sip from his tea cup.>\n\nWhat a delightful stroll!', 36734), -- An Uneventful Stroll
(57460, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tea ready! Tubbins give to Theotar!', 36734), -- Tubbins's Tea
(57442, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Gubbins and Tubbins speak in unison.>\n\nDis not good.', 36734), -- Lost in the Desiccation
(57426, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Exposure to the Light is clearly causing Theotar to lose control of himself.>\n\nJustice... for parasols... everywhere...', 36734), -- My Terrible Morning
(57427, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Exposure to the Light is clearly causing Theotar to lose control of himself.>\n\nMy... sincerest apologies...', 36734), -- Unbearable Light
(57428, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Exposure to the Light is clearly causing Theotar to lose control of himself.>\n\nGubbins... Where are you?', 36734), -- Theotar's Mission
(57405, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well, aren\'t you an unexpected windfall?\n\nI\'m afraid I\'ve no tea to offer you at the present. Forgive my poor manners.', 36734), -- Chasing Madness
(57380, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This bad paper look very bad...', 36734), -- Sign Your Own Death Warrant
(57240, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You no go here. Here for bad buds!', 36734), -- Where is Prince Renathal?
(59256, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This medallion will serve us well. But we lack our leader to don it.\n\nWe must seek out more allies.', 36734), -- The Fearstalker
(59209, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our numbers are bolstered. Our survival chance is only slightly less grim.', 36734), -- Rebel Reinforcements
(57189, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sounds like it worked better than expected. \n\nPerfect. The Fearstalker stands no chance.', 36734), -- Breaking the Hopebreakers
(57190, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The devourers will rip them to shreds.', 36734), -- They Won't Know What Hit Them
(60313, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad you made it here alive.\n\nGeneral Draven has informed me of a plan that might just work.', 36734), -- Dredhollow
(57159, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We barely made it. Denathrius will surely be on our trail soon.', 36734), -- A Reflection of Truth
(60506, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We meet again. Under dire circumstances I fear.', 36734), -- The Accuser
(57136, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. The fear we struck allowed us to extract ample anima for Revendreth.\n\nOnto our final target.', 36734), -- The Penitent Hunt
(57164, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Once you master fear, all crumble before you.', 36734), -- Devour This
(57131, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Perhaps in death you will make a fine hunter.\n\nI can practically taste the fear we will inflict.', 36734), -- Let the Hunt Begin
(59014, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us begin, shall we?', 36734), -- King of the Hill
(58941, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that Duskterror is captured, we have a little more control over these grounds.', 36734), -- Alpha Bat
(58916, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This soul is nearly ready. \n\nWe have an opportunity to finish preparing this one and take care of a problem in the process.', 36734), -- Dread Priming
(57098, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Grove of Terror.\n\nHere you will see the beginning of the process for the anima you seek.', 36734), -- The Grove of Terror
(59232, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am nothing if not merciful and understanding.\n\nThe Accuser will be given every opportunity to repent her errors and learn from them.', 36734), -- A Lesson in Humility
(57182, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sire Denathrius smiles as you hand him the medallion.>\n\nI am pleased to see that you can be trusted with great power.', 36734), -- The Accuser's Fate
(57180, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Lord Chamberlain smiles wryly.>\n\nThe Halls of Atonement are under my control.', 36734), -- The Accuser's Secret
(57176, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is, in fact, one of the larger sinstones I have seen.\n\nThis will be easy to exploit.', 36734); -- Sinstone Delivery
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(59023, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lord Chamberlain confirmed the kill. We should hurry.', 36734), -- Ending the Inquisitor
(57175, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As Echelon holds the sinstone fragments, anima binds draw the pieces into one another, reforming into a completed sinstone.>\n\nWe are ready to proceed.', 36734), -- Inquisitor Vilhelm's Sinstone
(59021, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The ward on the Accuser\'s sinstone is weakened by the inquisitor\'s death.\n\nBut we must kill both inquisitors before the ward will fully fall, and we can access the Accuser\'s sinstone.', 36734), -- Herald Their Demise
(58932, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Echelon eyes Temel suspiciously.>\n\nI never liked this runt.', 36734), -- Temel, the Sin Herald
(58931, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Temel will know how to exploit this sinstone.', 36734), -- Inquisitor Stelia's Sinstone
(57173, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that truly the best you have to offer?', 36734), -- The Accuser's Sinstone
(57161, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Echelon grunts.> You\'re late.', 36734), -- I Don't Get My Hands Dirty
(57179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now, Maw Walker, arise as a weapon of ordained power within my dominion.', 36734), -- The Authority of Revendreth
(57178, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wait! Please, Maw Walker, allow me to announce you to the Master.', 36734), -- The Master Awaits
(58654, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, the peasants have asked for help have they? \n\nThose who are loyal would know that sacrifices are essential to the survival of Revendreth. Yes, these are dark times with anima and new souls both being in short supply. \n\nBut we must all do our part, no matter how painful.', 36734), -- A Plea to the Harvesters
(57174, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is all that remains of our tithe? The Tithelord is not one for excuses. We may need to gather a second tithe quickly or he will condemn us all to the Ember Ward.', 36734), -- The Stoneborn
(56978, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It may not look like it, but this rebellion is on its last leg. Those who stand against the Master are fools who will know a new form of pain and suffering.', 36734), -- To Darkhaven
(58433, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, mortal. Stoneborn require anima to exist. Without it, they return to their stone form. This supply hurt them more than destroying thirty of their rebels.', 36734), -- Anima Attrition
(56955, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your talents in combat show promise. Perhaps with a few more centuries and a little humility we might make something of you.', 36734), -- Rebels on the Road
(56942, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are not getting the carriage through that.', 36734), -- On The Road Again
(56829, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah good. No one got ate.\n\nCarriage is ready to go when you are.', 36734), -- Bottom Feeders
(57381, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was FUN! I have not felt so alive in centuries. Everything about you is just... different, and invigorating.\n\nI can continue to assist you until you are ready to leave the Endmire but then we will need to part ways for a time. I have some unfinished business regarding someone who put me in a cage.', 36734), -- The Greatest Duelist
(57007, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh good, still not dead yet?\n\nYou see where the Lord Chamberlain or Cudgelface landed?', 36734), -- Invitation of the Master
(57026, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hopefully these wretched creatures did not bore you with their inane babble.', 36734), -- The Sinstone
(57025, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sorry for the state of things. Usually a venthyr would be here to greet you. Been a while since we seen anyone come through that gate.\n\nAll good, though, as I know the welcome speech better than a good mornin\' whipping.', 36734), -- A Plea to Revendreth
(58724, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What has transpired in Ardenweald? Tell me everything.', 36734), -- The Queen's Request
(62807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many cries call in the night. Many creatures seek shelter.\n\nThis is a refreshing breeze.', 36734), -- Forest Refugees
(58723, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Banished One stirs and Ardenweald\'s power withers in drought.', 36734), -- The Court of Winter
(58721, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Winter Queen turns her gaze upon you.>\n\nHow curious to see someone like you in my forest.', 36734), -- Awaken the Dreamer
(60661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met, stranger. You arrive in... interesting times.\n\n<Herne snorts a laugh.>\n\nAnd with equally interesting company.', 36734), -- Dying Dreams
(58869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have won the battle...\n\n...But I fear we may have lost Ysera.', 36734), -- Battle for Hibernal Hollow
(60621, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This attack... It is like they are being driven!', 36734), -- Enemies at the Gates
(58720, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These Drust thought to send a force to strike us from behind. \n\n<Korayn smirks.>\n\nYour call brought my fellow huntsmen and huntresses to reinforce us. Our foes were the ones caught by surprise.', 36734), -- Missing!
(58719, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Wild Hunt rides to our aid... but not from the west?\n\nThat is where Hunt-Captain Korayn was tracking a dangerous foe. She and her hunting party must have been waylaid.', 36734), -- The Droman's Call
(58714, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These Drust are bold to send spies into my grove! Very bold... and very foolish.', 36734), -- The Forest Has Eyes
(58593, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a terrible end for such a majestic spirit... \n\nBut that was why she connected with you! Because you are of the same world! Azeroth!\n\nNow, I can finally feel her nightmares wane. At last, she knows some peace.\n\nThank you, my friend.', 36734), -- End of the Dream
(58590, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We all start somewhere. Sometimes in unexpected places. Me, I just popped out of the ground like a flower.', 36734), -- Visions of the Dreamer: Origins
(60578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To have an old friend turn against you, in the most terrible way. How very painful. \n\nBut we are so close now, to soothing the spirit within the wildseed.', 36734), -- Visions of the Dreamer: The Betrayal
(58591, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is just the beginning of their attack. But it is still a heavy blow dealt to them. Thank you.', 36734), -- Despoilers
(58589, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re a natural at this. Now we can bring the spirit\'s nightmares into the open and deal with them directly.\n\nIf we succeed, she will be so much more at peace.', 36734), -- The Restless Dreamer
(58592, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those Drust really are cruel to us fae! Those spirit tenders were just trying to do their job...\n\nThank you for helping them.', 36734), -- Caring for the Caretakers
(60572, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'re ready to begin preparing for the ritual? Wonderful.\n\nI am also ready!', 36734), -- For the Sake of Spirit
(58524, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found and took their anima right from the heart of the grove? Impressive.\n\nDreamweaver will be most pleased. But I expect that we will soon encounter some unhappy visitors.\n\nWe must move quickly to aid the spirit in this wildseed... before we are overrun.', 36734), -- Sparkles Rain from Above
(58488, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that we have the heart, we need to find a way out of this place.\n\nAnd I hear the distinct sound of approaching enemies...', 36734), -- Go for the Heart
(58486, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We made it to the heart. Well done.\n\nIf that is what all the Drust are truly like, then Ardenweald is in a dire situation, indeed.', 36734), -- He's Drust in the Way
(58480, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Drust have stolen more anima than I expected. To think that they have deprived us of this much in the midst of a drought...\n\nWe must take back whatever we can. Not only for the sake of the wildseed, but to also thwart whatever the Drust intend to do.', 36734), -- Read the Roots
(58483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you.\n\nI know these are just objects, but they mean so much. Sometimes just holding a piece of one\'s past can be a comfort.\n\nIt means not everything is lost.', 36734), -- Mementos
(58484, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This anima will help Dreamweaver complete his ritual... and perhaps save spirits who otherwise would have been lost.\n\nGood work.', 36734), -- Take What You Can
(58473, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never thought I would return to Tirna Noch. The place of so many memories. So many regrets...\n\nBut now is not the time for sentimentality. Now is the time for action.', 36734), -- Echoes of Tirna Noch
(60905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s going to be difficult, but I know of a place where there may be enough anima to help this wildseed.', 36734), -- Infusing the Wildseed
(60901, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dreamweaver has told me much about your strange wildseed. \n\nI will do what I can to help.', 36734), -- Passage to Hibernal Hollow
(60881, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see part of the Wild Hunt\'s strength restored... and also that you found the spirit cradle of use.\n\nNow let us bring the wildseed within it to Hibernal Hollow.', 36734), -- Ride of the Wild Hunt
(60856, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work, $n. This won\'t win our war... but it will at least help us in the fight for Soryn\'s Meadow.', 36734), -- Toppling the Brute
(60839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for rescuing my fellow hunters. We\'ll have time to respect those who have returned to the cycle when this is all over.', 36734), -- Remnants of the Wild Hunt
(60764, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s good to see you again. The Wild Hunt could use your help.', 36734), -- Soothing Song
(60738, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m surprised that any wildseed could spawn such nightmares.', 36734), -- The Way to Hibernal Hollow
(60520, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There, that seems to have calmed her. I can feel her dreams begin to ease.\n\nYou really do have a knack for this!\n\nBut I\'m worried that we\'re only buying time, and we need to do something more drastic.', 36734), -- Nightmares Manifest
(60522, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you have a spirit cradle! That will be quite useful, indeed.\n\nAssuming we can calm this chaos, of course. The wildseed you bonded with is having intense nightmares... and they\'re manifesting all over the grove!', 36734), -- Return to Tirna Vaal
(60632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It cannot be easy for Korayn to hunt one of our own... but she is right. The forest is not safe so long as Lorkron lurks within it.\n\nWhat a terrible fate... both for those who become possessed, and those who must hunt them down.', 36734), -- I Know Your Face
(60631, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have slain so many, and yet more remain. We must get to the heart of this evil and tear it out.\n\nIf we don\'t, then soon it could spread all across Ardenweald.', 36734), -- Big Problem, Little Vorkai
(60630, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If it was not clear before, it is now. This is a personal hunt.\n\nWe will rid Ardenweald of this monster.', 36734), -- Totem Eclipse
(60628, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only Ara\'lon and Lumera survived? The rest have fallen?\n\n<Korayn trembles with unbridled fury.> \n\nI will see to it that their bodies are retrieved. And this cannot go unpunished. We will avenge them all!', 36734), -- The Missing Hunters
(60629, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found far more weapons than I expected.\n\nVery strange. How could they acquire so many of OUR blades?\n\n<Korayn appears troubled.>\n\nThey will be used against our enemies again, I swear it.', 36734), -- Extreme Recycling
(60521, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lady Moonberry said she would be sending a strong hand to help secure this grove.\n\nNow, how are you in a fight?', 36734), -- Call of the Hunt
(60519, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gone so soon... the forest must be in even more dire straits than I realized.\n\n<Moonberry looks crestfallen for a moment before resolutely setting her hands on her hips.>\n\nWell, then we\'ll just have to help ease the Queen\'s burden. Then she\'ll have the time to grant you an audience!', 36734), -- Audience with the Winter Queen
(60724, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shadows loom over the weald, harbingers of tragedy to come.\n\nThe river of fate flows swiftly, its currents inexorable. Where they lead... cannot yet be seen.', 36734), -- Heartless
(60709, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve lost so much. Why would anyone do this?', 36734), -- Recovering the Heart
(60671, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The heart of the grove...\n\nWe have to get it back... for all those who have fallen.', 36734), -- The Sacrifices We Must Make
(60648, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Derawyn... I can\'t lose her too! We can use the animacones to save her!', 36734), -- Survivors of Heartwood Grove
(60647, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many animacones lost... at least we were able to recover these.', 36734), -- Recovering the Animacones
(60638, 4, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found more wildseeds! They\'re so weak... I can\'t stand to see them like this.\n\nWe need to finish this and bring them to Tirna Vaal as soon as possible.', 36734), -- Recovering Wildseeds
(60639, 18, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Korenth is... gone? And the heart of the grove has been taken?\n\nThen... then we have much to do.', 36734), -- Heart of the Grove
(60637, 66, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. I tried so hard to save them... but once that mask is on, there is no return.', 36734), -- The End of Former Friends
(60624, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can\'t leave Heartwood Grove like this.', 36734), -- Ride to Heartwood Grove
(60600, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Shadows loom over Heartwood Grove. Things unseen crawl within the darkness.', 36734), -- Preparing for the Winter Queen
(60594, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Starlight shines within Dreamweaver, radiant and serene.\n\nAnd... two rivers meet in a lush delta. A wildseed and a mortal, both new to the forest. Bonded by spirit and by fate.\n\nLong has it been since the boughs beheld such an event. The weald will be watching.', 36734), -- One Special Spirit
(60577, 273, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The animacones! In this time of drought, we have to scrounge for every bit of anima we can get. Thank you.', 36734), -- Hungry for Animacones
(60575, 273, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work. This should help get the Tranquil Pools back to normal.\n\nI admit, I had thought the worst when I couldn\'t find any of the tenders. I\'m glad they were only eaten by the local vegetation.', 36734), -- Belly Full of Fae
(60563, 1, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work. We mustn\'t stop tending to the wildseeds that the Winter Queen has chosen to be saved.\n\nNow, perhaps you can lend me a hand with another matter.', 36734), -- Tending to Wildseeds
(60567, 6, 274, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Normally, I wouldn\'t require help from whatever race you are.\n\nAh... my apologies. That was rude.\n\nPlease understand that Ardenweald is home to souls from across all of the mortal realm. It\'s hard for me to keep track of every race that arrives here.', 36734), -- Shooing Wildlife
(57816, 1, 273, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 0, 'You\'re new, aren\'t you? Not a fae, not a soul, nor are you bound for a wildseed.\n\nAnd the droman sent you here to help me? Well, this just got very interesting.', 36734), -- Dreamweaver
(57951, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'From acorns grow forests, from souls comes vital anima. Small though they be, on them our fates depend.\n\nThe forest sighs in gratitude.', 36734), -- Souls Come Home
(57950, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gone! The bad spriggan is gone! Spirit Glen will be ours again.\n\nNow to leave. We have to leave.', 36734), -- Mizik the Haughty
(57949, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Stolen! They stole the anima! They ran like crazy and...\n\nWait that\'s normal. They\'re always that bad. Stupid spriggans!', 36734), -- They Need to Calm Down
(57948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found them! You found my friends! They have their forms!\n\nNow we have one last thing to do. One last thing!', 36734), -- Nothing Left to Give
(57947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this? What\'s this?\n\nThe Tall Tree has sent you to help us? Help us!', 36734), -- Spirits of the Glen
(57787, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Featherlight says you\'ve kept up your end of our deal. That\'s great to hear!\n\nI have some news to share about getting you an audience with the Queen.', 36734), -- Keep to the Path
(60859, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s been a while since a new soul arrived in Ardenweald, so each one already here is precious to us.\n\nI\'ll be sure to let Lady Moonberry know of your heroic rescue efforts on her behalf. She might even decide she owes you a favor!', 36734), -- Souls of the Forest
(60857, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Droman Krelnor sighs wearily as he reads the short list of wildseeds.>\n\nAt least a few will be relocated to Tirna Vaal.', 36734), -- We Can't Save Them All
(60778, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was fun to watch! You had that bird ready to build a nest and raise hatchlings!\n\nOh, how I needed that laugh...', 36734), -- Wildseed Rescue
(60341, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you can handle the spriggans, then perhaps I can give you some of the more interesting items on Lady Moonberry\'s agenda. Excellent!', 36734), -- First on the Agenda
(60763, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope that your arrival in Ardenweald is a sign that better times are on the horizon.', 36734), -- I Moustache You to Lend a Hand
(60338, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We haven\'t seen anyone come through the gateway in a very long time! Certainly not someone like you.\n\nWhat brings you to Ardenweald?', 36734), -- Journey to Ardenweald
(61716, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A troubling vision indeed. But we must not give up hope.', 36710), -- A Glimpse into Darkness
(61715, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Even through his scarred, molten visage, the emotion on Bolvar\'s face is plain.>\n\nMy daughter... here. I never thought...', 36710), -- Request of the Highlord
(59206, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad of your return, mortal.\n\nI pray you were successful in preventing the advent of war between Bastion and Maldraxxus.', 36710), -- Words of the Primus
(60737, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The runeblade glows brighter as you approach an old stone altar.>', 36710), -- The Door to the Unknown
(59011, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are struggling to hold the line. We need to act fast.', 36710), -- In Death We Are Truly Tested
(59974, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot allow this wound to fester any longer. I will burn it closed here and now!', 36710), -- A Soul Saved
(62654, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You return in one piece. And with not just Darion, but his father as well. You continue to succeed, Maw Walker.', 36710), -- Maw Walker
(61190, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now to get you and your... associates out of here.', 36710), -- Wake of Ashes
(59973, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I cannot thank you enough, $n.', 36710), -- A Bond Beyond Death
(59966, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My father... Alexandros Mograine. The Ashbringer.\n\nI... never expected to see him again.', 36710), -- Delving Deeper
(59962, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Keep up. We have little time.', 36710), -- Hope Never Dies
(59959, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My, my. Today certainly has been full of surprises!\n\nNow, mortal, I\'m curious what has brought you back to the Maw.', 36710), -- The Brand Holds the Key
(59960, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Darion is trapped within the cage. He appears unconscious.>', 36710), -- A Cooling Trail
(60972, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The amulet glows red.>', 36710), -- The Hunt for the Baron
(59897, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The area is quiet. There is no sign of your allies.>', 36710), -- Seeking the Baron
(59874, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What news from Maldraxxus, $n?\n\n<Bolvar listens to your tale.>', 36710), -- The Maw
(59202, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will have my soldiers honor Krexus as he deserves.', 36710), -- Among the Chosen
(59009, 274, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to have allies. Even ones so stubborn.', 36710), -- Her Rightful Place
(59025, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Cursed lich--may his soul never be reborn.', 36710), -- Straight to the Heart
(59190, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Vengeance is nearly ours.', 36710), -- Seek Your Mark
(59188, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes... They will be made to know our pain.', 36710), -- Vaunted Vengeance
(59185, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He will not escape this time.', 36710), -- Entangling Web
(59210, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well executed.', 36710), -- Tainted Cores
(59172, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Draka may be content to forget our master, but I will not rest until he is avenged.', 36710), -- War is Deception
(58821, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A simple task for such a storied hero.', 36710), -- Glorious Pursuits
(59171, 574, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, these will do nicely.', 36710), -- Prey Upon Them
(58751, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Be thankful I am the one you found here.\n\nOthers in Maldraxxus may not have seen the potential in your strength.', 36710), -- A Common Peril
(59231, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see you\'ve made a new ally... of a sort. And another rune has been empowered.', 36710), -- Fathomless Power
(60831, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah... apprentice? Are you there? I feel... strange.', 36710), -- Fit For a Margrave
(59223, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Come, my apprentice! Our efforts nearly bear fruit!', 36710), -- By Any Other Name
(58031, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh--and what are these?', 36710), -- Applied Science
(58045, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our slimes will be safe, my dear apprentice!', 36710), -- Plague is Thicker Than Water
(58036, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You and your slime are bonding!', 36710), -- Hazardous Waste Collection
(60733, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By blood and thunder, we will crush our foes.', 36710), -- Front and Center
(58027, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a precious slime!', 36710), -- Slime, Anyone?
(58011, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found my venom sacs! What a helpful apprentice you are!', 36710), -- Bug Bites
(58016, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Such marvelous spores, my apprentice!', 36710), -- Spores Galore
(59130, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My apprentice! I have been searching everywhere for you!', 36710), -- The House of Plagues
(57994, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We escaped!\n\nWe will recuperate here for now. At least until we find a way to return to Bastion.\n\nThank you for showing me what courage is, my friend.', 36710), -- In The Flesh
(57993, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sense something within this construct... something familiar...', 36710), -- Two of Them, Two of Us
(57982, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems these kyrian are more stalwart than I expected. Let us avenge their fallen kin.', 36710), -- Breaking Down Barriers
(57987, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Complacency is every soldier\'s worst enemy. No one is safe in times of war, not even within the walls of their own fortress.', 36710), -- A Deadly Distraction
(57985, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Slowing the production of new constructs should earn our soldiers some reprieve, however brief.', 36710), -- Give Them a Hand
(57986, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. Though they are lost, at least their remains will not be defiled.', 36710), -- A Burden Worth Bearing
(57984, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems one of the house\'s barons is overseeing this operation... and he is unaware that we are free. \n\nWe have a chance to strike him down!', 36710), -- The Ones in Charge
(57983, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only four survivors... I know I should be grateful that there were any at all, but...\n\nWhat sort of monsters would do this to anyone, let alone to their own people?', 36710), -- Archon Save Us
(59616, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your voice... you are not one of the Maldraxxi?', 36710), -- Army of One
(57979, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your leadership is inspiring. These troops would follow you anywhere!', 36710), -- Offensive Behavior
(58268, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With that ridge clear, we\'ll be safe to advance.', 36710), -- Take the High Ground
(60557, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our forces stand ready to fight once more!', 36710), -- First Time? You Have to Fight!
(57976, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should strike fear into their stolen hearts.', 36710), -- Lead By Example
(57912, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I expect much of you, mortal. Help lead our frontal assault on the construct forces!', 36710), -- Baron of the Chosen
(60886, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We cannot lose sight of the battles ahead of us. The door will have to wait.', 36710), -- The Seat of the Primus
(60461, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Show me this runeblade of yours, mortal.', 36710), -- Meet the Margrave
(60453, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You wield a fine weapon. Now you must put it to use.', 36710), -- The Path to Glory
(60428, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Primus was always fond of his trials. It seems you\'ve passed this one. Well done.', 36710), -- The Blade of the Primus
(58726, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You work quickly, don\'t you? I could use more assistants like you.', 36710), -- Thick Skin
(58618, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good! I knew that beast would prove no challenge for you.', 36710), -- Ossein Enchantment
(58616, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is going to take a bit of work.', 36710), -- Forging a Champion
(57516, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This blade was inside the stone all this time... \n\nMargrave Krexus was right about your potential.', 36710), -- Through the Fire and Flames
(60451, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work. I see that our defenses have been shored up.', 36710), -- Never Enough
(58617, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should ensure we stand ready for war.', 36710), -- Maintaining Order
(58351, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If they cannot properly evade detection, then they do not deserve to survive.', 36710), -- The Hills Have Eyes
(57514, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Mark my words, recruit. We will crush the other houses for their acts of treason.', 36710), -- The First Act of War
(57515, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Chosen are all that remains of what the Primus stood for.\n\nWe are the last hope of this realm.', 36710), -- The House of the Chosen
(60181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A threat removed for the House of the Chosen, and new recruits that show potential.\n\nGood work.', 36710), -- Trench Warfare
(57511, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And now we test them.', 36710), -- Arms for the Poor
(60179, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Many strive for greatness in Maldraxxus. Few truly achieve infamy.\n\nLet us see if our names will one day be remembered.', 36710), -- Memory of Honor
(57512, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Everything in this land is dangerous. There is no room for weakness.', 36710), -- Walk Among Death
(57425, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'In ages past, the Primus founded that tournament to showcase the might of Maldraxxus. \n\nToday, it has sparked an all-out war.', 36710), -- Land of Opportunity
(60021, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good, the crowd\'s on your side.\n\nNow there\'s just one last test.', 36710), -- Champion the Cause
(60020, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Still walking on two legs? My hopes for you are rising.', 36710), -- An Opportunistic Strike
(57390, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You survived? Really...\n\nI admit, that was unexpected.', 36710), -- To Die By the Sword
(57386, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well? Why aren\'t you out there fighting?', 36710), -- If You Want Peace...
(61107, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The way is open. The eternal battlefields of Maldraxxus await you.', 36710), -- A Land of Strife
(61096, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This slot shall suffice.', 36710), -- The Arbiter's Will
(60056, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I know why you have come. This kyrian has explained much.', 36710), -- Follow the Path
(60055, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thanikos... is gone... isn\'t he.', 36710), -- A Time for Courage
(60054, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our only move now is forward, outsider.', 36710), -- The Final Countdown
(60053, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not fully charged, but close enough! May have to disable a few safety features...', 36710), -- Clear as Crystal
(60052, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Resonator is working at full capacity and our foes are dispatched. Excellent.', 36710), -- Double Tap
(60007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was fast! Well done, well done indeed!', 36710), -- Stay Scrappy
(60009, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a true ally, outsider. Thank you.', 36710), -- Fight Another Day
(60008, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You fight with the poise of a true kyrian, outsider.', 36710), -- Rip and Tear
(60006, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have bought a staging ground, but much remains to be done.', 36710), -- Now or Never
(60005, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not quite the army I hoped would come, but I welcome your blade by my side.', 36710), -- Imminent Danger
(59200, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'It seems the Forsworn are in our very midst, even in the Spires.\n\nWe must send aid to the Temple of Courage posthaste.', 36710), -- The Wards of Bastion
(59199, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Archon\'s grace is upon you, mortal.', 36710), -- Kyrestia, the Firstborne
(59198, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Archon\'s chambers are just above. I urge you to practice extreme deference while in her presence.', 36710), -- On Swift Wings
(59197, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kalisthene has vouched for you by allowing usage of the beacon. For that reason, you have my attention.', 36710), -- Steward at Work
(59426, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whenever you need assistance, your steward will be available to provide many services.', 36710), -- Your Personal Assistant
(62170, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, these wise words are certainly Eurgon\'s. I\'m happy to report he made it home.', 36710), -- You'll Never Walk Alone
(59196, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Polemarch? He is the right hand of the Archon!\n\nShe truly believes us. We still have a chance!', 36710), -- Go in Service
(57568, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With the crook and Korinna\'s guidance, I can begin to bring this place and its creatures back to their former state of respite. Thank you, $n.', 36710), -- Tough Love
(57547, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I told you she can be quite the troublemaker. Ugh, Kala!', 36710), -- A Test of Courage
(57545, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Kala! Look! $n brought back your favorite things!', 36710), -- Distractions for Kala
(57538, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We can now better fulfill our duties here. I look forward to resuming my meditations. Thank you.', 36710), -- Disturbing the Peace
(57529, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, you\'re here to lend a hand? Wonderful!', 36710), -- Garden in Turmoil
(60013, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We must hurry. The Archon must know what transpired here.', 36710), -- Leave it to Mnemis
(60180, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope your experience was satisfactory.', 36710), -- A Paragon's Reflection
(58843, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am very pleased to meet you. The Vault has not received visitors in some time.', 36710), -- The Vault of the Archon
(58980, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your search was fruitful. I am delighted to see you remain intact.', 36710), -- Mnemis, At Your Service
(58979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you will forgive my behavior. I was not feeling quite like myself.', 36710), -- I MADE You!
(58978, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mikanikos fumes silently.>', 36710), -- Lysonia's Truth
(58977, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it. With any luck, her memories are within our grasp.', 36710), -- What's In a Memory?
(58800, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I love the hum of anima. It has been a long time since I have heard it in such abundance.', 36710), -- The Mnemonic Locus
(58799, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Their anima will be put to better use.', 36710), -- The Prime's Directive
(58771, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You found it! And other interesting tomes as well. They will be properly catalogued when we are done.', 36710), -- Directions Not Included
(58976, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Mikanikos gestures irritably toward the Forsworn behind him.>\n\nAre you here to help fix THIS?', 36710), -- Chasing a Memory
(62714, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this?\n\n<She opens the parcel. A soft smile spreads over her face.>\n\nThis is wonderful. Thank you.', 36710), -- A Gift for an Acolyte
(60466, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These are perfect! Go in service, always.', 36710), -- The Old Ways
(60316, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh! Broke praetor is gone? Sad. So sad. But thank you-hoo!', 36710), -- WANTED: Altered Sentinel
(57444, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw them perish. It is more than they deserved.', 36710), -- An Inspired Moral Inventory
(57447, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will see not a moment\'s rest today, will we?\n\n<Kleia eyes the fragment warily.>', 36710), -- Purity's Prerogative
(57269, 669, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That you should join us now, on the precipice of this treachery, is curious.\n\n<The Paragon of Purity studies you with a piercing gaze.>\n\nYou have done well. The Archon will know of your contributions this day.', 36710), -- The Hand of Doubt
(57446, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our fight is not yet over, $n.', 36710), -- The Enemy You Know
(57037, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I can hear their song once more. It is a boon on my mind, but the loudest voice remains. We must silence it before it destroys all that we hold dear.', 36710), -- A Once Sweet Sound
(57719, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These words... this voice...\n\nHow do I know this voice?', 36710), -- Dangerous Discourse
(59147, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some stains must be scoured away.', 36710), -- The Hand of Purification
(57717, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Eridia grips her hammer with pale knuckles.>\n\nHow... how are they so numerous?', 36710), -- Step Back From That Ledge, My Friend
(57716, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for bringing him to me, $n. He is in a worse state than any of us might have guessed.', 36710), -- A Wayward Disciple?
(57264, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your service is noted. Thank you.', 36710), -- On the Edge of a Revelation
(57977, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have proven yourself adept at this task. You have my gratitude.', 36710), -- A Temple in Need
(57270, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for volunteering.', 36710), -- The Temple of Purity
(58174, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kleia smiles warmly at you.>\n\nDoes this mean you intend to stay?', 36710), -- All An Aspirant Can Do
(60218, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are worthy of Bastion\'s grace, $n. May it serve you well.', 36710), -- The Archon's Answer
(57266, 669, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a moment worthy of celebration, $n.\n\n<Kleia smiles broadly at you.>\n\nYou have done it. They have come.', 36710), -- The First Cleansing
(57291, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gather yourself. This is how you will find your way before the Archon. I am certain of it.', 36710), -- The Chamber of First Reflection
(57714, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is always a painful lesson. We do not think less of you for it.', 36710), -- Assessing Your Spirit
(57909, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'To fight so many, in so short a time, is truly a feat of stamina.\n\nI am tired just looking at you.\n\n<Pelagos laughs.>', 36710), -- Assessing Your Stamina
(57288, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Impressive. I see I have little enough to teach you.', 36710), -- Assessing Your Strength
(57908, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Forgelite\'s gratitude goes deeper than you know.\n\nNow. You must turn your attention back to our purpose here.', 36710), -- The True Crucible Awaits
(57713, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you like it. It is far from my finest work, but it will serve you well while you are here.', 36710), -- The Work of One's Hands
(59920, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am deeply grateful for your help. Now I can practice my craft again!', 36710), -- Light the Forge, Forgelite
(57265, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That is... somehow more and less than I expected. It will have to do.', 36710), -- The Cycle of Anima: Drought Conditions
(57263, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sika pokes the squishy substance.>\n\nIt glows. This means anima. Forgelite will be pleased.', 36710), -- The Cycle of Anima: Etherwyrms
(57267, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh. They smell nice! And they glow lots.\n\nThis is good. Yes.', 36710), -- The Cycle of Anima: Flower Power
(57711, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello again! This one is glad to see you!', 36710), -- A Forge Gone Cold
(57710, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I confess... I was hoping for a small spectacle to lift the spirits of the aspirants in my care.\n\nI was not expecting to have my own lifted, as well. Thank you for that.', 36710), -- A Life of Service
(57709, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<The Forgelite studies you for a moment, then nods.>\n\nWelcome. You are not what we expected, but we are glad to have you nonetheless.', 36710), -- The Aspirant's Crucible
(57676, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The things that bind us can be violent. The insight we gain is no reason to let them run rampant.', 36710), -- The Things That Haunt Us
(57677, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I owe you a great debt, $n.', 36710), -- A Soulbind In Need
(60156, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Purpose be praised! Your path becomes clearer.', 36710), -- The Path to Bastion
(60154, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your path and that of the Purpose are becoming one.', 36710), -- Understanding the Shadowlands
(60152, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We hope you are comfortable here, $n.\n\nConsider these ancient facilities to be at your disposal.', 36710), -- The Eternal City
(60151, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your path and the Purpose are now entwining.', 36710), -- A Doorway Through the Veil
(60150, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n! I am relieved you survived that realm of darkness.\n\nI am eager to hear the tale.', 36710), -- Tether to Home
(60149, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We may find a shared cause in the Purpose. It has sent you to us.', 36710), -- Audience with the Arbiter
(60148, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally, the Purpose may be guiding us again.', 36710), -- No Place for the Living
(60129, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Could it be? An actual mortal being in the Eternal City? The Purpose be served!', 36710), -- Stranger in an Even Stranger Land
(62484, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I was not expecting that!', 36710), -- Werk In Progress
(61114, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... This is from one of our own... from within the city walls.\n\nI will send word to our patrols. Remain alert, $n.\n\nShould the Scourge rise from within our own ranks, find me at once!', 36710), -- A Hunger for Flesh
(60871, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'These are grim tidings, $p. It seems the Banshee has aligned herself with a darker power than we know.', 36710), -- With Hope in Hand
(60932, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'It seems that eliminating the herald has slowed the Scourge\'s advance.\n\nWe will have to remain vigilant. Thank you for all you have done, $p.', 36710), -- Only Shadows Remain
(60867, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With their numbers momentarily reduced, now is our chance to strike.', 36710), -- A Message from Above
(62225, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Light, you have returned unharmed!\n\nWere you able to learn anything about what the cult is doing?', 36710), -- Bursting the Bubble
(60861, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<This news is rather unsettling.>', 36710), -- Secrets in Shadows
(62185, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my gratitude.\n\nI assure you this will not be forgotten.', 36710), -- Fighting for Attention
(60843, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These should suffice.', 36710), -- Cult Couture
(60828, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our scouts report increased activity among the Cult of the Damned.\n\nI believe it is time we learn exactly what our fanatical friends are planning.', 36710), -- A New Foothold
(62157, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They must be planning something. Though what, I cannot say.\n\nI will instruct our scouts to observe and report.', 36710), -- Scouting from a Safe Distance
(60003, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ll see to it they receive proper attention.', 36710); -- A Valiant Effort
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(60169, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It appears we are making headway.', 36710), -- Securing the Area
(59877, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You arrive just in time. Commander Gregor spoke highly of you.', 36710), -- A Message from Icecrown
(60767, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will see to it that King Greymane and the Lord Commander receive these reports, though I fear this is only the beginning.\n\nThis courier has just brought us dire news from Icecrown.\n\nIt appears we are not the only ones under assault.', 36710), -- Return of the Scourge
(60766, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $c. We will need all the strength we can muster in the coming days.', 36710), -- Damned Intruders
(59876, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is far worse than we thought.\n\nCommander Gregor must be told of the true extent of the Scourge\'s resurgence.', 36710), -- Field Reports
(60117, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, I was told to expect the arrival of a seasoned $c.\n\nLet\'s get to work.', 36710), -- Return of the Crusade
(60116, 1, 1, -1, -1, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'We must find a way to rescue Anduin and the others. But in this moment, the safety of our citizens and our allies is our highest priority.\n\nAs such, I have reached out to those experienced in dealing with threats of this nature.', 36710), -- Cause for Distraction
(60113, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew you would not hesitate to answer the call, $n.\n\nI will be brief.', 36710), -- An Urgent Request
(60869, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'This is troubling news, $p. To think that Sylvanas would willingly ally with such a dark power...', 36665), -- With Hope in Hand
(62163, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am glad for your return, $n.', 36665); -- A Message from the Justicar
